module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Filter

-- | A filter used to limit results when describing inbound or outbound
--   cross-cluster connections. Multiple values can be specified per
--   filter. A cross-cluster connection must match at least one of the
--   specified values for it to be returned from an operation.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newFilter</a> smart constructor.
data Filter
Filter' :: Maybe (NonEmpty Text) -> Maybe Text -> Filter

-- | Contains one or more values for the filter.
[$sel:values:Filter'] :: Filter -> Maybe (NonEmpty Text)

-- | The name of the filter.
[$sel:name:Filter'] :: Filter -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Filter</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:values:Filter'</a>, <a>filter_values</a> - Contains one or
--   more values for the filter.
--   
--   <a>$sel:name:Filter'</a>, <a>filter_name</a> - The name of the filter.
newFilter :: Filter

-- | Contains one or more values for the filter.
filter_values :: Lens' Filter (Maybe (NonEmpty Text))

-- | The name of the filter.
filter_name :: Lens' Filter (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Filter.Filter
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Filter.Filter

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.InboundConnectionStatus

-- | The connection status of an inbound cross-cluster connection.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newInboundConnectionStatus</a> smart constructor.
data InboundConnectionStatus
InboundConnectionStatus' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe InboundConnectionStatusCode -> InboundConnectionStatus

-- | Verbose information for the inbound connection status.
[$sel:message:InboundConnectionStatus'] :: InboundConnectionStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The state code for the inbound connection. Can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by the
--   remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by the remote
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Inbound connection provisioning is in progress.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Inbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Inbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:statusCode:InboundConnectionStatus'] :: InboundConnectionStatus -> Maybe InboundConnectionStatusCode

-- | Create a value of <a>InboundConnectionStatus</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:InboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>inboundConnectionStatus_message</a> - Verbose information for the
--   inbound connection status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusCode:InboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>inboundConnectionStatus_statusCode</a> - The state code for the
--   inbound connection. Can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by the
--   remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by the remote
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Inbound connection provisioning is in progress.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Inbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Inbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
newInboundConnectionStatus :: InboundConnectionStatus

-- | Verbose information for the inbound connection status.
inboundConnectionStatus_message :: Lens' InboundConnectionStatus (Maybe Text)

-- | The state code for the inbound connection. Can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by the
--   remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by the remote
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Inbound connection provisioning is in progress.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Inbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Inbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
inboundConnectionStatus_statusCode :: Lens' InboundConnectionStatus (Maybe InboundConnectionStatusCode)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.InboundConnectionStatus.InboundConnectionStatus
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.InboundConnectionStatus.InboundConnectionStatus
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.InboundConnectionStatus.InboundConnectionStatus
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.InboundConnectionStatus.InboundConnectionStatus
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.InboundConnectionStatus.InboundConnectionStatus
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.InboundConnectionStatus.InboundConnectionStatus
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.InboundConnectionStatus.InboundConnectionStatus


module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.InboundConnection

-- | Details of an inbound connection.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newInboundConnection</a> smart constructor.
data InboundConnection
InboundConnection' :: Maybe DomainInformationContainer -> Maybe DomainInformationContainer -> Maybe Text -> Maybe InboundConnectionStatus -> InboundConnection

-- | The <tt> AWSDomainInformation </tt> for the remote OpenSearch domain.
[$sel:remoteDomainInfo:InboundConnection'] :: InboundConnection -> Maybe DomainInformationContainer

-- | The <tt> AWSDomainInformation </tt> for the local OpenSearch domain.
[$sel:localDomainInfo:InboundConnection'] :: InboundConnection -> Maybe DomainInformationContainer

-- | The connection ID for the inbound cross-cluster connection.
[$sel:connectionId:InboundConnection'] :: InboundConnection -> Maybe Text

-- | The <tt> InboundConnectionStatus </tt> for the outbound connection.
[$sel:connectionStatus:InboundConnection'] :: InboundConnection -> Maybe InboundConnectionStatus

-- | Create a value of <a>InboundConnection</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:remoteDomainInfo:InboundConnection'</a>,

--   AWSDomainInformation </tt> for the remote OpenSearch domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:localDomainInfo:InboundConnection'</a>,
--   <a>inboundConnection_localDomainInfo</a> - The <tt>
--   AWSDomainInformation </tt> for the local OpenSearch domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:connectionId:InboundConnection'</a>,
--   <a>inboundConnection_connectionId</a> - The connection ID for the
--   inbound cross-cluster connection.
--   
--   <a>$sel:connectionStatus:InboundConnection'</a>,
--   <a>inboundConnection_connectionStatus</a> - The <tt>
--   InboundConnectionStatus </tt> for the outbound connection.

-- | The <tt> AWSDomainInformation </tt> for the local OpenSearch domain.

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType

-- | Type of log file. Can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>INDEX_SLOW_LOGS: Index slow logs contain insert requests that took
--   more time than configured index query log threshold to execute.</li>
--   <li>SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS: Search slow logs contain search queries that
--   took more time than configured search query log threshold to
--   execute.</li>
--   <li>ES_APPLICATION_LOGS: OpenSearch application logs contain
--   information about errors and warnings raised during the operation of
--   the service and can be useful for troubleshooting.</li>
--   <li>AUDIT_LOGS: Audit logs contain records of user requests for access
--   from the domain.</li>
--   </ul>
newtype LogType
LogType' :: Text -> LogType
[fromLogType] :: LogType -> Text
pattern LogType_AUDIT_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_ES_APPLICATION_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_INDEX_SLOW_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS :: LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.ToXML Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.XML.FromXML Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSONKey Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSONKey Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.Query.ToQuery Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.Headers.ToHeader Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.Log.ToLog Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.ByteString.ToByteString Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.Text.ToText Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Network.AWS.Data.Text.FromText Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance GHC.Classes.Ord Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.LogType.LogType

--   </ul>

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OptionStatus

-- | Provides the current status of the entity.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOptionStatus</a> smart constructor.
data OptionStatus
OptionStatus' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Natural -> POSIX -> POSIX -> OptionState -> OptionStatus

-- | Indicates whether the domain is being deleted.
[$sel:pendingDeletion:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The latest version of the entity.
[$sel:updateVersion:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> Maybe Natural

-- | The timestamp of when the entity was created.
[$sel:creationDate:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> POSIX

-- | The timestamp of the last time the entity was updated.
[$sel:updateDate:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> POSIX

-- | Provides the <tt>OptionState</tt> for the domain.
[$sel:state:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> OptionState

-- | Create a value of <a>OptionStatus</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:pendingDeletion:OptionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>optionStatus_pendingDeletion</a> - Indicates whether the domain is
--   being deleted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateVersion:OptionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>optionStatus_updateVersion</a> - The latest version of the entity.
--   
--   <a>$sel:creationDate:OptionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>optionStatus_creationDate</a> - The timestamp of when the entity
--   was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateDate:OptionStatus'</a>, <a>optionStatus_updateDate</a> -
--   The timestamp of the last time the entity was updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:state:OptionStatus'</a>, <a>optionStatus_state</a> - Provides
--   the <tt>OptionState</tt> for the domain.
newOptionStatus :: UTCTime -> UTCTime -> OptionState -> OptionStatus

-- | Indicates whether the domain is being deleted.
optionStatus_pendingDeletion :: Lens' OptionStatus (Maybe Bool)

-- | The latest version of the entity.
optionStatus_updateVersion :: Lens' OptionStatus (Maybe Natural)

-- | The timestamp of when the entity was created.
optionStatus_creationDate :: Lens' OptionStatus UTCTime

-- | The timestamp of the last time the entity was updated.
optionStatus_updateDate :: Lens' OptionStatus UTCTime

-- | Provides the <tt>OptionState</tt> for the domain.
optionStatus_state :: Lens' OptionStatus OptionState
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OptionStatus.OptionStatus

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.AdvancedOptionsStatus

-- | Status of the advanced options for the specified domain. Currently,
--   the following advanced options are available:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Option to allow references to indices in an HTTP request body.
--   Must be <tt>false</tt> when configuring access to individual
--   sub-resources. By default, the value is <tt>true</tt>. See <a>Advanced
--   cluster parameters</a> for more information.</li>
--   <li>Option to specify the percentage of heap space allocated to field
--   data. By default, this setting is unbounded.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Advanced cluster parameters</a>.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAdvancedOptionsStatus</a> smart constructor.
data AdvancedOptionsStatus

--   domain.

-- | Create a value of <a>AdvancedOptionsStatus</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:options:AdvancedOptionsStatus'</a>,
--   <a>advancedOptionsStatus_options</a> - The status of advanced options
--   for the specified domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:AdvancedOptionsStatus'</a>,
--   <a>advancedOptionsStatus_status</a> - The <tt>OptionStatus</tt> for
--   advanced options for the specified domain.
newAdvancedOptionsStatus :: OptionStatus -> AdvancedOptionsStatus

-- | The <tt>OptionStatus</tt> for advanced options for the specified
--   domain.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:options:AccessPoliciesStatus'</a>,
--   <a>accessPoliciesStatus_options</a> - The access policy configured for
--   the domain. Access policies can be resource-based, IP-based, or
--   IAM-based. See <a>Configuring access policies</a>for more information.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:AccessPoliciesStatus'</a>,
--   <a>accessPoliciesStatus_status</a> - The status of the access policy
--   for the domain. See <tt>OptionStatus</tt> for the status information
--   that's included.
newAccessPoliciesStatus :: Text -> OptionStatus -> AccessPoliciesStatus

-- | The access policy configured for the domain. Access policies can be
--   resource-based, IP-based, or IAM-based. See <a>Configuring access
--   policies</a>for more information.
accessPoliciesStatus_options :: Lens' AccessPoliciesStatus Text

-- | The status of the access policy for the domain. See
--   <tt>OptionStatus</tt> for the status information that's included.
accessPoliciesStatus_status :: Lens' AccessPoliciesStatus OptionStatus
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.AccessPoliciesStatus.AccessPoliciesStatus
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.AccessPoliciesStatus.AccessPoliciesStatus
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.AccessPoliciesStatus.AccessPoliciesStatus
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.AccessPoliciesStatus.AccessPoliciesStatus
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.AccessPoliciesStatus.AccessPoliciesStatus

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OutboundConnectionStatus

-- | The connection status of an outbound cross-cluster connection.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOutboundConnectionStatus</a> smart constructor.
data OutboundConnectionStatus
OutboundConnectionStatus' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe OutboundConnectionStatusCode -> OutboundConnectionStatus

-- | Verbose information for the outbound connection status.
[$sel:message:OutboundConnectionStatus'] :: OutboundConnectionStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The state code for the outbound connection. Can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by the remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Outbound connection has been approved by the remote
--   domain owner for getting provisioned.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Outbound connection rejection by remote domain owner is
--   in progress.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by remote domain
--   owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:statusCode:OutboundConnectionStatus'] :: OutboundConnectionStatus -> Maybe OutboundConnectionStatusCode

-- | Create a value of <a>OutboundConnectionStatus</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:OutboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>outboundConnectionStatus_message</a> - Verbose information for the
--   outbound connection status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusCode:OutboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>outboundConnectionStatus_statusCode</a> - The state code for the
--   outbound connection. Can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by the remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Outbound connection has been approved by the remote
--   domain owner for getting provisioned.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Outbound connection rejection by remote domain owner is
--   in progress.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by remote domain
--   owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
newOutboundConnectionStatus :: OutboundConnectionStatus

-- | Verbose information for the outbound connection status.
outboundConnectionStatus_message :: Lens' OutboundConnectionStatus (Maybe Text)

-- | The state code for the outbound connection. Can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by the remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Outbound connection has been approved by the remote
--   domain owner for getting provisioned.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Outbound connection rejection by remote domain owner is
--   in progress.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by remote domain
--   owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
outboundConnectionStatus_statusCode :: Lens' OutboundConnectionStatus (Maybe OutboundConnectionStatusCode)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OutboundConnectionStatus.OutboundConnectionStatus
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OutboundConnectionStatus.OutboundConnectionStatus
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OutboundConnectionStatus.OutboundConnectionStatus
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OutboundConnectionStatus.OutboundConnectionStatus
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OutboundConnectionStatus.OutboundConnectionStatus
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OutboundConnectionStatus.OutboundConnectionStatus
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.OutboundConnectionStatus.OutboundConnectionStatus

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.PackageDetails

-- | Basic information about a package.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPackageDetails</a> smart constructor.
data PackageDetails
PackageDetails' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe PackageType -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe PackageStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ErrorDetails -> Maybe Text -> PackageDetails

-- | Internal ID of the package.
[$sel:packageID:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Currently supports only TXT-DICTIONARY.
[$sel:packageType:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe PackageType
[$sel:lastUpdatedAt:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The timestamp of when the package was created.
[$sel:createdAt:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe POSIX

-- | User-specified name of the package.
[$sel:packageName:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Current state of the package. Values are COPYING, COPY_FAILED,
--   AVAILABLE, DELETING, and DELETE_FAILED.
[$sel:packageStatus:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe PackageStatus

-- | User-specified description of the package.
[$sel:packageDescription:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Additional information if the package is in an error state. Null
--   otherwise.
[$sel:errorDetails:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe ErrorDetails
[$sel:availablePackageVersion:PackageDetails'] :: PackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>PackageDetails</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   - Internal ID of the package.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageType:PackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>packageDetails_packageType</a> - Currently supports only
--   TXT-DICTIONARY.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedAt:PackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>packageDetails_lastUpdatedAt</a> - Undocumented member.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdAt:PackageDetails'</a>, <a>packageDetails_createdAt</a>
--   - The timestamp of when the package was created.

--   <a>packageDetails_packageName</a> - User-specified name of the
--   package.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageStatus:PackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>packageDetails_packageStatus</a> - Current state of the package.
--   Values are COPYING, COPY_FAILED, AVAILABLE, DELETING, and
--   DELETE_FAILED.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageDescription:PackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>packageDetails_packageDescription</a> - User-specified description
--   of the package.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorDetails:PackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>packageDetails_errorDetails</a> - Additional information if the
--   package is in an error state. Null otherwise.
--   
--   <a>$sel:availablePackageVersion:PackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>packageDetails_availablePackageVersion</a> - Undocumented member.

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails

-- | Information on a package associated with a domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDomainPackageDetails</a> smart constructor.
data DomainPackageDetails
DomainPackageDetails' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe PackageType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe DomainPackageStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ErrorDetails -> Maybe Text -> DomainPackageDetails

-- | The timestamp of the most recent update to the package association
--   status.
[$sel:lastUpdated:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The internal ID of the package.
[$sel:packageID:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Currently supports only TXT-DICTIONARY.
[$sel:packageType:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe PackageType

-- | User-specified name of the package.
[$sel:packageName:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text
[$sel:packageVersion:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | State of the association. Values are ASSOCIATING, ASSOCIATION_FAILED,
--   ACTIVE, DISSOCIATING, and DISSOCIATION_FAILED.
[$sel:domainPackageStatus:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe DomainPackageStatus

-- | The name of the domain you've associated a package with.
[$sel:domainName:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Additional information if the package is in an error state. Null
--   otherwise.
[$sel:errorDetails:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe ErrorDetails

-- | The relative path on Amazon OpenSearch Service nodes, which can be
--   used as synonym_path when the package is a synonym file.
[$sel:referencePath:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DomainPackageDetails</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdated:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_lastUpdated</a> - The timestamp of the most
--   recent update to the package association status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageID:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageID</a> - The internal ID of the
--   package.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageType:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageType</a> - Currently supports only
--   TXT-DICTIONARY.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageName:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageName</a> - User-specified name of the
--   package.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageVersion:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageVersion</a> - Undocumented member.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainPackageStatus:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_domainPackageStatus</a> - State of the
--   association. Values are ASSOCIATING, ASSOCIATION_FAILED, ACTIVE,
--   DISSOCIATING, and DISSOCIATION_FAILED.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainName:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_domainName</a> - The name of the domain you've
--   associated a package with.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorDetails:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_errorDetails</a> - Additional information if
--   the package is in an error state. Null otherwise.
--   
--   <a>$sel:referencePath:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_referencePath</a> - The relative path on
--   Amazon OpenSearch Service nodes, which can be used as synonym_path
--   when the package is a synonym file.
newDomainPackageDetails :: DomainPackageDetails

-- | The timestamp of the most recent update to the package association
--   status.
domainPackageDetails_lastUpdated :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The internal ID of the package.
domainPackageDetails_packageID :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)

-- | Currently supports only TXT-DICTIONARY.
domainPackageDetails_packageType :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe PackageType)

-- | User-specified name of the package.
domainPackageDetails_packageName :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)

-- | Undocumented member.
domainPackageDetails_packageVersion :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)

-- | State of the association. Values are ASSOCIATING, ASSOCIATION_FAILED,
--   ACTIVE, DISSOCIATING, and DISSOCIATION_FAILED.
domainPackageDetails_domainPackageStatus :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe DomainPackageStatus)

-- | The name of the domain you've associated a package with.
domainPackageDetails_domainName :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)

-- | Additional information if the package is in an error state. Null
--   otherwise.
domainPackageDetails_errorDetails :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe ErrorDetails)

-- | The relative path on Amazon OpenSearch Service nodes, which can be
--   used as synonym_path when the package is a synonym file.
domainPackageDetails_referencePath :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainPackageDetails.DomainPackageDetails

--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newReservedInstanceOffering</a> smart constructor.
data ReservedInstanceOffering

-- | The currency code for the reserved OpenSearch instance offering.

-- | The OpenSearch instance type offered by the reserved instance
--   offering.

-- | The charge to your account regardless of whether you are creating any
--   domains using the instance offering.
[$sel:recurringCharges:ReservedInstanceOffering'] :: ReservedInstanceOffering -> Maybe [RecurringCharge]

-- | The rate you are charged for each hour the domain that is using the
--   offering is running.
[$sel:usagePrice:ReservedInstanceOffering'] :: ReservedInstanceOffering -> Maybe Double

-- | The OpenSearch reserved instance offering identifier.
[$sel:reservedInstanceOfferingId:ReservedInstanceOffering'] :: ReservedInstanceOffering -> Maybe Text

-- | The upfront fixed charge you will pay to purchase the specific
--   reserved OpenSearch instance offering.
[$sel:fixedPrice:ReservedInstanceOffering'] :: ReservedInstanceOffering -> Maybe Double

-- | The duration, in seconds, for which the offering will reserve the
--   OpenSearch instance.
[$sel:duration:ReservedInstanceOffering'] :: ReservedInstanceOffering -> Maybe Int

[$sel:paymentOption:ReservedInstanceOffering'] :: ReservedInstanceOffering -> Maybe ReservedInstancePaymentOption

--   fields omitted.

--   
--   <a>$sel:instanceType:ReservedInstanceOffering'</a>,
--   <a>reservedInstanceOffering_instanceType</a> - The OpenSearch instance
--   type offered by the reserved instance offering.
--   
--   <a>$sel:recurringCharges:ReservedInstanceOffering'</a>,

--   account regardless of whether you are creating any domains using the

--   
--   <a>$sel:usagePrice:ReservedInstanceOffering'</a>,

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ReservedInstance

-- | Details of a reserved OpenSearch instance.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newReservedInstance</a> smart constructor.
data ReservedInstance
ReservedInstance' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe OpenSearchPartitionInstanceType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Integer -> Maybe [RecurringCharge] -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Int -> Maybe ReservedInstancePaymentOption -> ReservedInstance

-- | The state of the reserved OpenSearch instance.
[$sel:state:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The currency code for the reserved OpenSearch instance offering.
[$sel:currencyCode:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The number of OpenSearch instances that have been reserved.
[$sel:instanceCount:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | The time the reservation started.
[$sel:startTime:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The OpenSearch instance type offered by the reserved instance
--   offering.
[$sel:instanceType:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe OpenSearchPartitionInstanceType

-- | The customer-specified identifier to track this reservation.
[$sel:reservationName:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Text
[$sel:billingSubscriptionId:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Integer

-- | The charge to your account regardless of whether you are creating any
--   domains using the instance offering.
[$sel:recurringCharges:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe [RecurringCharge]

-- | The rate you are charged for each hour for the domain that is using
--   this reserved instance.
[$sel:usagePrice:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Double

-- | The unique identifier for the reservation.
[$sel:reservedInstanceId:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The offering identifier.
[$sel:reservedInstanceOfferingId:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Text

-- | The upfront fixed charge you will paid to purchase the specific
--   reserved OpenSearch instance offering.
[$sel:fixedPrice:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Double

-- | The duration, in seconds, for which the OpenSearch instance is
--   reserved.
[$sel:duration:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Int

-- | The payment option as defined in the reserved OpenSearch instance
--   offering.
[$sel:paymentOption:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe ReservedInstancePaymentOption

-- | Create a value of <a>ReservedInstance</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--

--   reserved OpenSearch instance offering.
--   
--   <a>$sel:instanceCount:ReservedInstance'</a>,
--   <a>reservedInstance_instanceCount</a> - The number of OpenSearch
--   instances that have been reserved.
--

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.SAMLOptionsInput

-- | The SAML application configuration for the domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSAMLOptionsInput</a> smart constructor.
data SAMLOptionsInput
SAMLOptionsInput' :: Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe SAMLIdp -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe Text -> SAMLOptionsInput

-- | The SAML master username, which is stored in the Amazon OpenSearch
--   Service domain's internal database.
[$sel:masterUserName:SAMLOptionsInput'] :: SAMLOptionsInput -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | True if SAML is enabled.
[$sel:enabled:SAMLOptionsInput'] :: SAMLOptionsInput -> Maybe Bool

-- | The SAML Identity Provider's information.
[$sel:idp:SAMLOptionsInput'] :: SAMLOptionsInput -> Maybe SAMLIdp

-- | Element of the SAML assertion to use for backend roles. Default is
--   roles.
[$sel:rolesKey:SAMLOptionsInput'] :: SAMLOptionsInput -> Maybe Text

-- | The backend role that the SAML master user is mapped to.
[$sel:masterBackendRole:SAMLOptionsInput'] :: SAMLOptionsInput -> Maybe Text

-- | The duration, in minutes, after which a user session becomes inactive.
--   Acceptable values are between 1 and 1440, and the default value is 60.
[$sel:sessionTimeoutMinutes:SAMLOptionsInput'] :: SAMLOptionsInput -> Maybe Int

-- | Element of the SAML assertion to use for username. Default is NameID.
[$sel:subjectKey:SAMLOptionsInput'] :: SAMLOptionsInput -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SAMLOptionsInput</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:masterUserName:SAMLOptionsInput'</a>,
--   <a>sAMLOptionsInput_masterUserName</a> - The SAML master username,
--   which is stored in the Amazon OpenSearch Service domain's internal
--   database.
--   
--   <a>$sel:enabled:SAMLOptionsInput'</a>, <a>sAMLOptionsInput_enabled</a>
--   - True if SAML is enabled.
--   
--   <a>$sel:idp:SAMLOptionsInput'</a>, <a>sAMLOptionsInput_idp</a> - The
--   SAML Identity Provider's information.
--   
--   <a>$sel:rolesKey:SAMLOptionsInput'</a>,
--   <a>sAMLOptionsInput_rolesKey</a> - Element of the SAML assertion to
--   use for backend roles. Default is roles.
--   
--   <a>$sel:masterBackendRole:SAMLOptionsInput'</a>,
--   <a>sAMLOptionsInput_masterBackendRole</a> - The backend role that the
--   SAML master user is mapped to.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sessionTimeoutMinutes:SAMLOptionsInput'</a>,
--   <a>sAMLOptionsInput_sessionTimeoutMinutes</a> - The duration, in
--   minutes, after which a user session becomes inactive. Acceptable
--   values are between 1 and 1440, and the default value is 60.
--   
--   <a>$sel:subjectKey:SAMLOptionsInput'</a>,
--   <a>sAMLOptionsInput_subjectKey</a> - Element of the SAML assertion to
--   use for username. Default is NameID.
newSAMLOptionsInput :: SAMLOptionsInput

--   Service domain's internal database.

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.AdvancedSecurityOptionsInput

-- | The advanced security configuration: whether advanced security is
--   enabled, whether the internal database option is enabled, master
--   username and password (if internal database is enabled), and master
--   user ARN (if IAM is enabled).
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAdvancedSecurityOptionsInput</a> smart constructor.

--   <a>advancedSecurityOptionsInput_internalUserDatabaseEnabled</a> - True
--   if the internal user database is enabled.
--

-- | Specifies details about the scheduled Auto-Tune action. See
--   <a>Auto-Tune for Amazon OpenSearch Service</a> for more information.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newScheduledAutoTuneDetails</a> smart constructor.

--   JVM_YOUNG_GEN_TUNING.

--   fields omitted.

--   description.

--   action scheduled for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:actionType:ScheduledAutoTuneDetails'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledAutoTuneDetails_actionType</a> - The Auto-Tune action

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ServiceSoftwareOptions

-- | The current options of an domain service software options.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newServiceSoftwareOptions</a> smart constructor.
data ServiceSoftwareOptions
ServiceSoftwareOptions' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe DeploymentStatus -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ServiceSoftwareOptions

-- | The timestamp, in Epoch time, until which you can manually request a
--   service software update. After this date, we automatically update your
--   service software.
[$sel:automatedUpdateDate:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The current service software version present on the domain.
[$sel:currentVersion:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | <tt>True</tt> if a service software is never automatically updated.
--   <tt>False</tt> if a service software is automatically updated after
--   <tt>AutomatedUpdateDate</tt>.
[$sel:optionalDeployment:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | The status of your service software update. This field can take the
--   following values: <tt> ELIGIBLE</tt>, <tt>PENDING_UPDATE</tt>,
--   <tt>IN_PROGRESS</tt>, <tt>COMPLETED</tt>, and <tt> NOT_ELIGIBLE</tt>.
[$sel:updateStatus:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe DeploymentStatus

-- | <tt>True</tt> if you're able to cancel your service software version
--   update. <tt>False</tt> if you can't cancel your service software
--   update.
[$sel:cancellable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | <tt>True</tt> if you're able to update your service software version.
--   <tt>False</tt> if you can't update your service software version.
[$sel:updateAvailable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | The description of the <tt>UpdateStatus</tt>.
[$sel:description:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | The new service software version if one is available.
[$sel:newVersion':ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ServiceSoftwareOptions</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:automatedUpdateDate:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_automatedUpdateDate</a> - The timestamp, in
--   Epoch time, until which you can manually request a service software
--   update. After this date, we automatically update your service
--   software.
--   
--   <a>$sel:currentVersion:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_currentVersion</a> - The current service
--   software version present on the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionalDeployment:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_optionalDeployment</a> - <tt>True</tt> if a
--   service software is never automatically updated. <tt>False</tt> if a
--   service software is automatically updated after
--   <tt>AutomatedUpdateDate</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateStatus:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_updateStatus</a> - The status of your
--   service software update. This field can take the following values:
--   <tt> ELIGIBLE</tt>, <tt>PENDING_UPDATE</tt>, <tt>IN_PROGRESS</tt>,

--   <a>$sel:cancellable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainEndpointOptions

-- | Options to configure the endpoint for the domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDomainEndpointOptions</a> smart constructor.
data DomainEndpointOptions
DomainEndpointOptions' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe TLSSecurityPolicy -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> DomainEndpointOptions

-- | Whether only HTTPS endpoint should be enabled for the domain.
[$sel:enforceHTTPS:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specify the TLS security policy to apply to the HTTPS endpoint of the
--   domain. Can be one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-0-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports TLSv1.0 and higher.</li>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-2-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports only TLSv1.2</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:tLSSecurityPolicy:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe TLSSecurityPolicy

-- | Whether to enable a custom endpoint for the domain.
[$sel:customEndpointEnabled:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | The fully qualified domain for your custom endpoint.
[$sel:customEndpoint:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | The ACM certificate ARN for your custom endpoint.
[$sel:customEndpointCertificateArn:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DomainEndpointOptions</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:enforceHTTPS:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_enforceHTTPS</a> - Whether only HTTPS
--   endpoint should be enabled for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tLSSecurityPolicy:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_tLSSecurityPolicy</a> - Specify the TLS
--   security policy to apply to the HTTPS endpoint of the domain. Can be
--   one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-0-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports TLSv1.0 and higher.</li>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-2-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports only TLSv1.2</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:customEndpointEnabled:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointEnabled</a> - Whether to enable
--   a custom endpoint for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customEndpoint:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_customEndpoint</a> - The fully qualified
--   domain for your custom endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customEndpointCertificateArn:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointCertificateArn</a> - The ACM
--   certificate ARN for your custom endpoint.
newDomainEndpointOptions :: DomainEndpointOptions

-- | Whether only HTTPS endpoint should be enabled for the domain.
domainEndpointOptions_enforceHTTPS :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specify the TLS security policy to apply to the HTTPS endpoint of the
--   domain. Can be one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-0-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports TLSv1.0 and higher.</li>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-2-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports only TLSv1.2</li>
--   </ul>
domainEndpointOptions_tLSSecurityPolicy :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe TLSSecurityPolicy)

-- | Whether to enable a custom endpoint for the domain.
domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointEnabled :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Bool)

-- | The fully qualified domain for your custom endpoint.
domainEndpointOptions_customEndpoint :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Text)

-- | The ACM certificate ARN for your custom endpoint.
domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointCertificateArn :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Text)

instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainEndpointOptions.DomainEndpointOptions

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Tag

-- | A key value pair for a resource tag.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTag</a> smart constructor.
data Tag
Tag' :: Text -> Text -> Tag

-- | The <tt>TagKey</tt>, the name of the tag. Tag keys must be unique for
--   the domain to which they are attached.
[$sel:key:Tag'] :: Tag -> Text

-- | The <tt>TagValue</tt>, the value assigned to the corresponding tag
--   key. Tag values can be null and don't have to be unique in a tag set.
--   For example, you can have a key value pair in a tag set of <tt>project
--   : Trinity</tt> and <tt>cost-center : Trinity</tt>
[$sel:value:Tag'] :: Tag -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>Tag</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:key:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_key</a> - The <tt>TagKey</tt>, the name
--   of the tag. Tag keys must be unique for the domain to which they are
--   attached.
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_value</a> - The <tt>TagValue</tt>, the
--   value assigned to the corresponding tag key. Tag values can be null
--   and don't have to be unique in a tag set. For example, you can have a
--   key value pair in a tag set of <tt>project : Trinity</tt> and
--   <tt>cost-center : Trinity</tt>
newTag :: Text -> Text -> Tag

-- | The <tt>TagKey</tt>, the name of the tag. Tag keys must be unique for
--   the domain to which they are attached.
tag_key :: Lens' Tag Text

-- | The <tt>TagValue</tt>, the value assigned to the corresponding tag
--   key. Tag values can be null and don't have to be unique in a tag set.
--   For example, you can have a key value pair in a tag set of <tt>project
--   : Trinity</tt> and <tt>cost-center : Trinity</tt>
tag_value :: Lens' Tag Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Tag.Tag
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.Tag.Tag

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem

-- | Represents a single step of the upgrade or upgrade eligibility check
--   workflow.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpgradeStepItem</a> smart constructor.
data UpgradeStepItem
UpgradeStepItem' :: Maybe UpgradeStatus -> Maybe Double -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe UpgradeStep -> UpgradeStepItem

-- | The current status of the upgrade. The status can take one of the
--   following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:upgradeStepStatus:UpgradeStepItem'] :: UpgradeStepItem -> Maybe UpgradeStatus

-- | The floating point value representing the progress percentage of a
--   particular step.
[$sel:progressPercent:UpgradeStepItem'] :: UpgradeStepItem -> Maybe Double

-- | A list of strings containing detailed information about the errors
--   encountered in a particular step.
[$sel:issues:UpgradeStepItem'] :: UpgradeStepItem -> Maybe [Text]

-- | One of three steps an upgrade or upgrade eligibility check goes
--   through:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PreUpgradeCheck</li>
--   <li>Snapshot</li>
--   <li>Upgrade</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:upgradeStep:UpgradeStepItem'] :: UpgradeStepItem -> Maybe UpgradeStep

-- | Create a value of <a>UpgradeStepItem</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeStepStatus:UpgradeStepItem'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeStepItem_upgradeStepStatus</a> - The current status of the
--   upgrade. The status can take one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:progressPercent:UpgradeStepItem'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeStepItem_progressPercent</a> - The floating point value
--   representing the progress percentage of a particular step.
--   
--   <a>$sel:issues:UpgradeStepItem'</a>, <a>upgradeStepItem_issues</a> - A
--   list of strings containing detailed information about the errors
--   encountered in a particular step.
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeStep:UpgradeStepItem'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeStepItem_upgradeStep</a> - One of three steps an upgrade or
--   upgrade eligibility check goes through:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PreUpgradeCheck</li>
--   <li>Snapshot</li>
--   <li>Upgrade</li>
--   </ul>
newUpgradeStepItem :: UpgradeStepItem

-- | The current status of the upgrade. The status can take one of the
--   following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
upgradeStepItem_upgradeStepStatus :: Lens' UpgradeStepItem (Maybe UpgradeStatus)

-- | The floating point value representing the progress percentage of a
--   particular step.
upgradeStepItem_progressPercent :: Lens' UpgradeStepItem (Maybe Double)

-- | A list of strings containing detailed information about the errors
--   encountered in a particular step.
upgradeStepItem_issues :: Lens' UpgradeStepItem (Maybe [Text])

-- | One of three steps an upgrade or upgrade eligibility check goes
--   through:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PreUpgradeCheck</li>
--   <li>Snapshot</li>
--   <li>Upgrade</li>
--   </ul>
upgradeStepItem_upgradeStep :: Lens' UpgradeStepItem (Maybe UpgradeStep)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeStepItem.UpgradeStepItem


module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory

-- | History of the last 10 upgrades and upgrade eligibility checks.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpgradeHistory</a> smart constructor.
data UpgradeHistory
UpgradeHistory' :: Maybe UpgradeStatus -> Maybe [UpgradeStepItem] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> UpgradeHistory

-- | The current status of the upgrade. The status can take one of the
--   following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:upgradeStatus:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe UpgradeStatus

-- | A list of <tt> UpgradeStepItem </tt> s representing information about
--   each step performed as part of a specific upgrade or upgrade
--   eligibility check.
[$sel:stepsList:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe [UpgradeStepItem]

-- | A string that briefly describes the upgrade.
[$sel:upgradeName:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe Text

-- | UTC timestamp at which the upgrade API call was made in
--   "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ" format.
[$sel:startTimestamp:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Create a value of <a>UpgradeHistory</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeStatus:UpgradeHistory'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeHistory_upgradeStatus</a> - The current status of the
--   upgrade. The status can take one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:stepsList:UpgradeHistory'</a>, <a>upgradeHistory_stepsList</a>
--   - A list of <tt> UpgradeStepItem </tt> s representing information
--   about each step performed as part of a specific upgrade or upgrade
--   eligibility check.
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeName:UpgradeHistory'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeHistory_upgradeName</a> - A string that briefly describes
--   the upgrade.
--   
--   <a>$sel:startTimestamp:UpgradeHistory'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeHistory_startTimestamp</a> - UTC timestamp at which the
--   upgrade API call was made in "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ" format.
newUpgradeHistory :: UpgradeHistory

-- | The current status of the upgrade. The status can take one of the
--   following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
upgradeHistory_upgradeStatus :: Lens' UpgradeHistory (Maybe UpgradeStatus)

-- | A list of <tt> UpgradeStepItem </tt> s representing information about
--   each step performed as part of a specific upgrade or upgrade
--   eligibility check.
upgradeHistory_stepsList :: Lens' UpgradeHistory (Maybe [UpgradeStepItem])

-- | A string that briefly describes the upgrade.
upgradeHistory_upgradeName :: Lens' UpgradeHistory (Maybe Text)

-- | UTC timestamp at which the upgrade API call was made in
--   "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ" format.
upgradeHistory_startTimestamp :: Lens' UpgradeHistory (Maybe UTCTime)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.UpgradeHistory.UpgradeHistory

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.EBSOptions

-- | Options to enable, disable, and specify the properties of EBS storage
--   volumes.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newEBSOptions</a> smart constructor.
data EBSOptions
EBSOptions' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe Int -> Maybe VolumeType -> Maybe Bool -> EBSOptions

-- | Integer to specify the size of an EBS volume.
[$sel:volumeSize:EBSOptions'] :: EBSOptions -> Maybe Int

-- | The IOPD for a Provisioned IOPS EBS volume (SSD).
[$sel:iops:EBSOptions'] :: EBSOptions -> Maybe Int

-- | The volume type for EBS-based storage.
[$sel:volumeType:EBSOptions'] :: EBSOptions -> Maybe VolumeType

-- | Whether EBS-based storage is enabled.
[$sel:eBSEnabled:EBSOptions'] :: EBSOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | Create a value of <a>EBSOptions</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:volumeSize:EBSOptions'</a>, <a>eBSOptions_volumeSize</a> -
--   Integer to specify the size of an EBS volume.
--   
--   <a>$sel:iops:EBSOptions'</a>, <a>eBSOptions_iops</a> - The IOPD for a
--   Provisioned IOPS EBS volume (SSD).
--   
--   <a>$sel:volumeType:EBSOptions'</a>, <a>eBSOptions_volumeType</a> - The
--   volume type for EBS-based storage.
--   
--   <a>$sel:eBSEnabled:EBSOptions'</a>, <a>eBSOptions_eBSEnabled</a> -
--   Whether EBS-based storage is enabled.
newEBSOptions :: EBSOptions

-- | Integer to specify the size of an EBS volume.
eBSOptions_volumeSize :: Lens' EBSOptions (Maybe Int)

-- | The IOPD for a Provisioned IOPS EBS volume (SSD).
eBSOptions_iops :: Lens' EBSOptions (Maybe Int)

-- | The volume type for EBS-based storage.
eBSOptions_volumeType :: Lens' EBSOptions (Maybe VolumeType)

-- | Whether EBS-based storage is enabled.
eBSOptions_eBSEnabled :: Lens' EBSOptions (Maybe Bool)

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ZoneAwarenessConfig

--   number of availability zones.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newZoneAwarenessConfig</a> smart constructor.
data ZoneAwarenessConfig
ZoneAwarenessConfig' :: Maybe Int -> ZoneAwarenessConfig

-- | An integer value to indicate the number of availability zones for a
--   domain when zone awareness is enabled. This should be equal to number
--   of subnets if VPC endpoints is enabled.
[$sel:availabilityZoneCount:ZoneAwarenessConfig'] :: ZoneAwarenessConfig -> Maybe Int

-- | Create a value of <a>ZoneAwarenessConfig</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.

--   indicate the number of availability zones for a domain when zone
--   awareness is enabled. This should be equal to number of subnets if VPC
--   endpoints is enabled.
newZoneAwarenessConfig :: ZoneAwarenessConfig

-- | An integer value to indicate the number of availability zones for a
--   domain when zone awareness is enabled. This should be equal to number
--   of subnets if VPC endpoints is enabled.

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfig

-- | The configuration for the domain cluster, such as the type and number
--   of instances.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newClusterConfig</a> smart constructor.
data ClusterConfig
ClusterConfig' :: Maybe Int -> Maybe OpenSearchPartitionInstanceType -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Int -> Maybe ColdStorageOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe OpenSearchPartitionInstanceType -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe ZoneAwarenessConfig -> Maybe Int -> Maybe OpenSearchWarmPartitionInstanceType -> ClusterConfig

-- | Total number of dedicated master nodes, active and on standby, for the
--   cluster.
[$sel:dedicatedMasterCount:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe Int

-- | The instance type for a dedicated master node.
[$sel:dedicatedMasterType:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe OpenSearchPartitionInstanceType

-- | A boolean value to indicate whether a dedicated master node is
--   enabled. See <a>Dedicated master nodes in Amazon OpenSearch
--   Service</a> for more information.
[$sel:dedicatedMasterEnabled:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe Bool

-- | The number of instances in the specified domain cluster.
[$sel:instanceCount:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe Int

-- | Specifies the <tt>ColdStorageOptions</tt> config for a Domain
[$sel:coldStorageOptions:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe ColdStorageOptions

-- | A boolean value to indicate whether zone awareness is enabled. See
--   <a>Configuring a multi-AZ domain in Amazon OpenSearch Service</a> for
--   more information.
[$sel:zoneAwarenessEnabled:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe Bool

-- | The instance type for an OpenSearch cluster. UltraWarm instance types
--   are not supported for data instances.
[$sel:instanceType:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe OpenSearchPartitionInstanceType

-- | True to enable UltraWarm storage.
[$sel:warmEnabled:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe Bool

-- | The zone awareness configuration for a domain when zone awareness is
--   enabled.
[$sel:zoneAwarenessConfig:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe ZoneAwarenessConfig

-- | The number of UltraWarm nodes in the cluster.
[$sel:warmCount:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe Int

-- | The instance type for the OpenSearch cluster's warm nodes.
[$sel:warmType:ClusterConfig'] :: ClusterConfig -> Maybe OpenSearchWarmPartitionInstanceType

-- | Create a value of <a>ClusterConfig</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:dedicatedMasterCount:ClusterConfig'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfig_dedicatedMasterCount</a> - Total number of dedicated
--   master nodes, active and on standby, for the cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dedicatedMasterType:ClusterConfig'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfig_dedicatedMasterType</a> - The instance type for a
--   dedicated master node.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dedicatedMasterEnabled:ClusterConfig'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfig_dedicatedMasterEnabled</a> - A boolean value to
--   indicate whether a dedicated master node is enabled. See <a>Dedicated
--   master nodes in Amazon OpenSearch Service</a> for more information.
--   
--   <a>$sel:instanceCount:ClusterConfig'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfig_instanceCount</a> - The number of instances in the
--   specified domain cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:coldStorageOptions:ClusterConfig'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfig_coldStorageOptions</a> - Specifies the
--   <tt>ColdStorageOptions</tt> config for a Domain
--   
--   <a>$sel:zoneAwarenessEnabled:ClusterConfig'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfig_zoneAwarenessEnabled</a> - A boolean value to
--   indicate whether zone awareness is enabled. See <a>Configuring a
--   multi-AZ domain in Amazon OpenSearch Service</a> for more information.
--   
--   <a>$sel:instanceType:ClusterConfig'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfig_instanceType</a> - The instance type for an
--   OpenSearch cluster. UltraWarm instance types are not supported for
--   data instances.
--   
--   <a>$sel:warmEnabled:ClusterConfig'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfig_warmEnabled</a> - True to enable UltraWarm storage.
--   
--   <a>$sel:zoneAwarenessConfig:ClusterConfig'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfig_zoneAwarenessConfig</a> - The zone awareness
--   configuration for a domain when zone awareness is enabled.
--   
--   <a>$sel:warmCount:ClusterConfig'</a>, <a>clusterConfig_warmCount</a> -
--   The number of UltraWarm nodes in the cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:warmType:ClusterConfig'</a>, <a>clusterConfig_warmType</a> -
--   The instance type for the OpenSearch cluster's warm nodes.
newClusterConfig :: ClusterConfig

-- | Total number of dedicated master nodes, active and on standby, for the
--   cluster.
clusterConfig_dedicatedMasterCount :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe Int)

-- | The instance type for a dedicated master node.
clusterConfig_dedicatedMasterType :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe OpenSearchPartitionInstanceType)

-- | A boolean value to indicate whether a dedicated master node is
--   enabled. See <a>Dedicated master nodes in Amazon OpenSearch
--   Service</a> for more information.
clusterConfig_dedicatedMasterEnabled :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe Bool)

-- | The number of instances in the specified domain cluster.
clusterConfig_instanceCount :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe Int)

-- | Specifies the <tt>ColdStorageOptions</tt> config for a Domain
clusterConfig_coldStorageOptions :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe ColdStorageOptions)

-- | A boolean value to indicate whether zone awareness is enabled. See
--   <a>Configuring a multi-AZ domain in Amazon OpenSearch Service</a> for
--   more information.
clusterConfig_zoneAwarenessEnabled :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe Bool)

-- | The instance type for an OpenSearch cluster. UltraWarm instance types
--   are not supported for data instances.
clusterConfig_instanceType :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe OpenSearchPartitionInstanceType)

-- | True to enable UltraWarm storage.
clusterConfig_warmEnabled :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe Bool)

-- | The zone awareness configuration for a domain when zone awareness is
--   enabled.
clusterConfig_zoneAwarenessConfig :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe ZoneAwarenessConfig)

-- | The number of UltraWarm nodes in the cluster.
clusterConfig_warmCount :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe Int)

-- | The instance type for the OpenSearch cluster's warm nodes.
clusterConfig_warmType :: Lens' ClusterConfig (Maybe OpenSearchWarmPartitionInstanceType)

instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfig.ClusterConfig
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfig.ClusterConfig

module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainStatus

-- | The current status of a domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDomainStatus</a> smart constructor.
data DomainStatus
DomainStatus' :: Maybe EBSOptions -> Maybe Text -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe AutoTuneOptionsOutput -> Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption) -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe SnapshotOptions -> Maybe CognitoOptions -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe VPCDerivedInfo -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text) -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text) -> Text -> Text -> Text -> ClusterConfig -> DomainStatus

-- | The <tt>EBSOptions</tt> for the specified domain.
[$sel:eBSOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe EBSOptions
[$sel:engineVersion:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The status of the <tt>NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</tt>.
[$sel:nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions

-- | IAM access policy as a JSON-formatted string.
[$sel:accessPolicies:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The current status of the domain's service software.
[$sel:serviceSoftwareOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe ServiceSoftwareOptions

-- | The current status of the domain's Auto-Tune options.
[$sel:autoTuneOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe AutoTuneOptionsOutput

-- | Log publishing options for the given domain.
[$sel:logPublishingOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption)

-- | The current status of the domain's advanced security options.
[$sel:advancedSecurityOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptions

-- | The domain creation status. <tt>True</tt> if the creation of a domain
--   is complete. <tt> False </tt> if domain creation is still in progress.
[$sel:created:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The status of the <tt>SnapshotOptions</tt>.
[$sel:snapshotOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe SnapshotOptions

-- | The <tt>CognitoOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Configuring Amazon Cognito authentication for
--   OpenSearch Dashboards</a>.
[$sel:cognitoOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe CognitoOptions

-- | The status of the <tt>EncryptionAtRestOptions</tt>.
[$sel:encryptionAtRestOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptions

-- | The domain deletion status. <tt>True</tt> if a delete request has been
--   received for the domain but resource cleanup is still in progress.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the domain has not been deleted. Once domain
--   deletion is complete, the status of the domain is no longer returned.
[$sel:deleted:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The <tt>VPCOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Launching your Amazon OpenSearch Service domains
--   using a VPC</a>.
[$sel:vPCOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe VPCDerivedInfo

-- | Map containing the domain endpoints used to submit index and search
--   requests. Example <tt>key, value</tt>:
--   <tt>'vpc','vpc-endpoint-h2dsd34efgyghrtguk5gt6j2foh4.us-east-1.es.amazonaws.com'</tt>.
[$sel:endpoints:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text)

-- | The current status of the domain's endpoint options.
[$sel:domainEndpointOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptions

-- | The status of the domain configuration. <tt>True</tt> if Amazon
--   OpenSearch Service is processing configuration changes. <tt>False</tt>
--   if the configuration is active.
[$sel:processing:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The domain endpoint that you use to submit index and search requests.
[$sel:endpoint:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The status of a domain version upgrade. <tt>True</tt> if Amazon
--   OpenSearch Service is undergoing a version upgrade. <tt>False</tt> if
--   the configuration is active.
[$sel:upgradeProcessing:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The status of the <tt>AdvancedOptions</tt>.
[$sel:advancedOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text)

-- | The unique identifier for the specified domain.
[$sel:domainId:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Text

-- | The name of a domain. Domain names are unique across the domains owned
--   by an account within an AWS region. Domain names start with a letter
--   or number and can contain the following characters: a-z (lowercase),
--   0-9, and - (hyphen).
[$sel:domainName:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a domain. See <a>IAM identifiers</a>
--   in the <i>AWS Identity and Access Management User Guide</i> for more
--   information.
[$sel:arn:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Text

-- | The type and number of instances in the domain.
[$sel:clusterConfig:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> ClusterConfig

-- | Create a value of <a>DomainStatus</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:eBSOptions:DomainStatus'</a>, <a>domainStatus_eBSOptions</a> -
--   The <tt>EBSOptions</tt> for the specified domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:engineVersion:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_engineVersion</a> - Undocumented member.
--   
--   <a>$sel:nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</a> - The status of the
--   <tt>NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:accessPolicies:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_accessPolicies</a> - IAM access policy as a
--   JSON-formatted string.
--   
--   <a>$sel:serviceSoftwareOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_serviceSoftwareOptions</a> - The current status of the
--   domain's service software.
--   
--   <a>$sel:autoTuneOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,

--   the given domain.

--   the domain's advanced security options.
--

--   domain creation status. <tt>True</tt> if the creation of a domain is
--   complete. <tt> False </tt> if domain creation is still in progress.

--   <a>domainStatus_snapshotOptions</a> - The status of the
--   <tt>SnapshotOptions</tt>.

--   <a>$sel:cognitoOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_cognitoOptions</a> - The <tt>CognitoOptions</tt> for

--   Cognito authentication for OpenSearch Dashboards</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:encryptionAtRestOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_encryptionAtRestOptions</a> - The status of the

--

--   domain deletion status. <tt>True</tt> if a delete request has been
--   received for the domain but resource cleanup is still in progress.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the domain has not been deleted. Once domain
--   deletion is complete, the status of the domain is no longer returned.
--   
--   <a>$sel:vPCOptions:DomainStatus'</a>, <a>domainStatus_vPCOptions</a> -

--

--   <tt>'vpc','vpc-endpoint-h2dsd34efgyghrtguk5gt6j2foh4.us-east-1.es.amazonaws.com'</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainEndpointOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_domainEndpointOptions</a> - The current status of the
--   domain's endpoint options.
--   
--   <a>$sel:processing:DomainStatus'</a>, <a>domainStatus_processing</a> -
--   The status of the domain configuration. <tt>True</tt> if Amazon
--   OpenSearch Service is processing configuration changes. <tt>False</tt>
--   if the configuration is active.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endpoint:DomainStatus'</a>, <a>domainStatus_endpoint</a> - The
--   domain endpoint that you use to submit index and search requests.
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeProcessing:DomainStatus'</a>,
