module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfigStatus

-- | The configuration status for the specified domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newClusterConfigStatus</a> smart constructor.
data ClusterConfigStatus
ClusterConfigStatus' :: ClusterConfig -> OptionStatus -> ClusterConfigStatus

-- | The cluster configuration for the specified domain.
[$sel:options:ClusterConfigStatus'] :: ClusterConfigStatus -> ClusterConfig

-- | The cluster configuration status for the specified domain.
[$sel:status:ClusterConfigStatus'] :: ClusterConfigStatus -> OptionStatus

-- | Create a value of <a>ClusterConfigStatus</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:options:ClusterConfigStatus'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfigStatus_options</a> - The cluster configuration for the
--   specified domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:status:ClusterConfigStatus'</a>,
--   <a>clusterConfigStatus_status</a> - The cluster configuration status
--   for the specified domain.
newClusterConfigStatus :: ClusterConfig -> OptionStatus -> ClusterConfigStatus

-- | The cluster configuration for the specified domain.
clusterConfigStatus_options :: Lens' ClusterConfigStatus ClusterConfig

-- | The cluster configuration status for the specified domain.
clusterConfigStatus_status :: Lens' ClusterConfigStatus OptionStatus
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfigStatus.ClusterConfigStatus
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfigStatus.ClusterConfigStatus
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfigStatus.ClusterConfigStatus
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfigStatus.ClusterConfigStatus
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfigStatus.ClusterConfigStatus
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfigStatus.ClusterConfigStatus
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.ClusterConfigStatus.ClusterConfigStatus


module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainConfig

-- | The configuration of a domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDomainConfig</a> smart constructor.
data DomainConfig
DomainConfig' :: Maybe EBSOptionsStatus -> Maybe VersionStatus -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptionsStatus -> Maybe AccessPoliciesStatus -> Maybe AutoTuneOptionsStatus -> Maybe LogPublishingOptionsStatus -> Maybe ClusterConfigStatus -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptionsStatus -> Maybe SnapshotOptionsStatus -> Maybe CognitoOptionsStatus -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptionsStatus -> Maybe VPCDerivedInfoStatus -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptionsStatus -> Maybe AdvancedOptionsStatus -> DomainConfig

-- | The <tt>EBSOptions</tt> for the domain.
[$sel:eBSOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe EBSOptionsStatus

-- | String of format Elasticsearch_X.Y or OpenSearch_X.Y to specify the
--   engine version for the OpenSearch or Elasticsearch domain.
[$sel:engineVersion:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe VersionStatus

-- | The <tt>NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</tt> for the domain.
[$sel:nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptionsStatus

-- | IAM access policy as a JSON-formatted string.
[$sel:accessPolicies:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe AccessPoliciesStatus

-- | Specifies <tt>AutoTuneOptions</tt> for the domain.
[$sel:autoTuneOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe AutoTuneOptionsStatus

-- | Log publishing options for the given domain.
[$sel:logPublishingOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe LogPublishingOptionsStatus

-- | The <tt>ClusterConfig</tt> for the domain.
[$sel:clusterConfig:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe ClusterConfigStatus

-- | Specifies <tt>AdvancedSecurityOptions</tt> for the domain.
[$sel:advancedSecurityOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptionsStatus

-- | The <tt>SnapshotOptions</tt> for the domain.
[$sel:snapshotOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe SnapshotOptionsStatus

-- | The <tt>CognitoOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Configuring Amazon Cognito authentication for
--   OpenSearch Dashboards</a>.
[$sel:cognitoOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe CognitoOptionsStatus

-- | The <tt>EncryptionAtRestOptions</tt> for the domain.
[$sel:encryptionAtRestOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptionsStatus

-- | The <tt>VPCOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Launching your Amazon OpenSearch Service domains
--   using a VPC</a>.
[$sel:vPCOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe VPCDerivedInfoStatus

-- | The <tt>DomainEndpointOptions</tt> for the domain.
[$sel:domainEndpointOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptionsStatus

-- | The <tt>AdvancedOptions</tt> for the domain. See <a>Advanced
--   options</a> for more information.
[$sel:advancedOptions:DomainConfig'] :: DomainConfig -> Maybe AdvancedOptionsStatus

-- | Create a value of <a>DomainConfig</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:eBSOptions:DomainConfig'</a>, <a>domainConfig_eBSOptions</a> -
--   The <tt>EBSOptions</tt> for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:engineVersion:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_engineVersion</a> - String of format Elasticsearch_X.Y
--   or OpenSearch_X.Y to specify the engine version for the OpenSearch or
--   Elasticsearch domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</a> - The
--   <tt>NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</tt> for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:accessPolicies:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_accessPolicies</a> - IAM access policy as a
--   JSON-formatted string.
--   
--   <a>$sel:autoTuneOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_autoTuneOptions</a> - Specifies
--   <tt>AutoTuneOptions</tt> for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:logPublishingOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_logPublishingOptions</a> - Log publishing options for
--   the given domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:clusterConfig:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_clusterConfig</a> - The <tt>ClusterConfig</tt> for the
--   domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:advancedSecurityOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_advancedSecurityOptions</a> - Specifies
--   <tt>AdvancedSecurityOptions</tt> for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:snapshotOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_snapshotOptions</a> - The <tt>SnapshotOptions</tt> for
--   the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cognitoOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_cognitoOptions</a> - The <tt>CognitoOptions</tt> for
--   the specified domain. For more information, see <a>Configuring Amazon
--   Cognito authentication for OpenSearch Dashboards</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:encryptionAtRestOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_encryptionAtRestOptions</a> - The
--   <tt>EncryptionAtRestOptions</tt> for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:vPCOptions:DomainConfig'</a>, <a>domainConfig_vPCOptions</a> -
--   The <tt>VPCOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Launching your Amazon OpenSearch Service domains
--   using a VPC</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainEndpointOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_domainEndpointOptions</a> - The
--   <tt>DomainEndpointOptions</tt> for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:advancedOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_advancedOptions</a> - The <tt>AdvancedOptions</tt> for
--   the domain. See <a>Advanced options</a> for more information.
newDomainConfig :: DomainConfig

-- | The <tt>EBSOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_eBSOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe EBSOptionsStatus)

-- | String of format Elasticsearch_X.Y or OpenSearch_X.Y to specify the
--   engine version for the OpenSearch or Elasticsearch domain.
domainConfig_engineVersion :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe VersionStatus)

-- | The <tt>NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptionsStatus)

-- | IAM access policy as a JSON-formatted string.
domainConfig_accessPolicies :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe AccessPoliciesStatus)

-- | Specifies <tt>AutoTuneOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_autoTuneOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe AutoTuneOptionsStatus)

-- | Log publishing options for the given domain.
domainConfig_logPublishingOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe LogPublishingOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>ClusterConfig</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_clusterConfig :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe ClusterConfigStatus)

-- | Specifies <tt>AdvancedSecurityOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_advancedSecurityOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>SnapshotOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_snapshotOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe SnapshotOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>CognitoOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Configuring Amazon Cognito authentication for
--   OpenSearch Dashboards</a>.
domainConfig_cognitoOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe CognitoOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>EncryptionAtRestOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_encryptionAtRestOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>VPCOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Launching your Amazon OpenSearch Service domains
--   using a VPC</a>.
domainConfig_vPCOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe VPCDerivedInfoStatus)

-- | The <tt>DomainEndpointOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_domainEndpointOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe DomainEndpointOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>AdvancedOptions</tt> for the domain. See <a>Advanced
--   options</a> for more information.
domainConfig_advancedOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe AdvancedOptionsStatus)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainConfig.DomainConfig
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainConfig.DomainConfig
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainConfig.DomainConfig
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainConfig.DomainConfig
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainConfig.DomainConfig
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainConfig.DomainConfig
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types.DomainConfig.DomainConfig


module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.Types

-- | API version <tt>2021-01-01</tt> of the Amazon OpenSearch Service SDK
--   configuration.
defaultService :: Service

-- | An exception for missing / invalid input fields. Gives http status
--   code of 400.
_ValidationException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An error occurred because user does not have permissions to access the
--   resource. Returns HTTP status code 403.
_AccessDeniedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An exception for creating a resource that already exists. Gives http
--   status code of 400.
_ResourceAlreadyExistsException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An error occurred because the client attempts to remove a resource
--   that is currently in use. Returns HTTP status code 409.
_ConflictException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An error occurred while processing the request.
_BaseException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An error occured because the client wanted to access a not supported
--   operation. Gives http status code of 409.
_DisabledOperationException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The request processing has failed because of an unknown error,
--   exception or failure (the failure is internal to the service) . Gives
--   http status code of 500.
_InternalException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An exception for trying to create or access sub-resource that is
--   either invalid or not supported. Gives http status code of 409.
_InvalidTypeException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An exception for accessing or deleting a resource that does not exist.
--   Gives http status code of 400.
_ResourceNotFoundException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The request processing has failed because of invalid pagination token
--   provided by customer. Returns an HTTP status code of 400.
_InvalidPaginationTokenException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An exception for trying to create more than allowed resources or
--   sub-resources. Gives http status code of 409.
_LimitExceededException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | The Auto-Tune desired state. Valid values are ENABLED and DISABLED.
newtype AutoTuneDesiredState
AutoTuneDesiredState' :: Text -> AutoTuneDesiredState
[fromAutoTuneDesiredState] :: AutoTuneDesiredState -> Text
pattern AutoTuneDesiredState_DISABLED :: AutoTuneDesiredState
pattern AutoTuneDesiredState_ENABLED :: AutoTuneDesiredState

-- | The Auto-Tune state for the domain. For valid states see <a>Auto-Tune
--   for Amazon OpenSearch Service</a>.
newtype AutoTuneState
AutoTuneState' :: Text -> AutoTuneState
[fromAutoTuneState] :: AutoTuneState -> Text
pattern AutoTuneState_DISABLED :: AutoTuneState
pattern AutoTuneState_DISABLED_AND_ROLLBACK_COMPLETE :: AutoTuneState
pattern AutoTuneState_DISABLED_AND_ROLLBACK_ERROR :: AutoTuneState
pattern AutoTuneState_DISABLED_AND_ROLLBACK_IN_PROGRESS :: AutoTuneState
pattern AutoTuneState_DISABLED_AND_ROLLBACK_SCHEDULED :: AutoTuneState
pattern AutoTuneState_DISABLE_IN_PROGRESS :: AutoTuneState
pattern AutoTuneState_ENABLED :: AutoTuneState
pattern AutoTuneState_ENABLE_IN_PROGRESS :: AutoTuneState
pattern AutoTuneState_ERROR :: AutoTuneState

-- | Type of log file. Can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>INDEX_SLOW_LOGS: Index slow logs contain insert requests that took
--   more time than configured index query log threshold to execute.</li>
--   <li>SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS: Search slow logs contain search queries that
--   took more time than configured search query log threshold to
--   execute.</li>
--   <li>ES_APPLICATION_LOGS: OpenSearch application logs contain
--   information about errors and warnings raised during the operation of
--   the service and can be useful for troubleshooting.</li>
--   <li>AUDIT_LOGS: Audit logs contain records of user requests for access
--   from the domain.</li>
--   </ul>
newtype LogType
LogType' :: Text -> LogType
[fromLogType] :: LogType -> Text
pattern LogType_AUDIT_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_ES_APPLICATION_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_INDEX_SLOW_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS :: LogType

-- | The state of a requested change. One of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Processing: The request change is still in progress.</li>
--   <li>Active: The request change is processed and deployed to the
--   domain.</li>
--   </ul>
newtype OptionState
OptionState' :: Text -> OptionState
[fromOptionState] :: OptionState -> Text
pattern OptionState_Active :: OptionState
pattern OptionState_Processing :: OptionState
pattern OptionState_RequiresIndexDocuments :: OptionState

-- | The rollback state while disabling Auto-Tune for the domain. Valid
--   values are NO_ROLLBACK and DEFAULT_ROLLBACK.
newtype RollbackOnDisable

[fromRollbackOnDisable] :: RollbackOnDisable -> Text
pattern RollbackOnDisable_DEFAULT_ROLLBACK :: RollbackOnDisable
pattern RollbackOnDisable_NO_ROLLBACK :: RollbackOnDisable

-- | Status of the advanced options for the specified domain. Currently,
--   the following advanced options are available:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>Option to allow references to indices in an HTTP request body.
--   Must be <tt>false</tt> when configuring access to individual
--   sub-resources. By default, the value is <tt>true</tt>. See <a>Advanced
--   cluster parameters</a> for more information.</li>
--   <li>Option to specify the percentage of heap space allocated to field
--   data. By default, this setting is unbounded.</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   For more information, see <a>Advanced cluster parameters</a>.

--   more information.

--   are not supported for data instances.

--   enabled.

--   The <tt>VPCOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Launching your Amazon OpenSearch Service domains
--   using a VPC</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainEndpointOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_domainEndpointOptions</a> - The
--   <tt>DomainEndpointOptions</tt> for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:advancedOptions:DomainConfig'</a>,
--   <a>domainConfig_advancedOptions</a> - The <tt>AdvancedOptions</tt> for
--   the domain. See <a>Advanced options</a> for more information.
newDomainConfig :: DomainConfig

-- | The <tt>EBSOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_eBSOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe EBSOptionsStatus)

-- | String of format Elasticsearch_X.Y or OpenSearch_X.Y to specify the
--   engine version for the OpenSearch or Elasticsearch domain.
domainConfig_engineVersion :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe VersionStatus)

-- | The <tt>NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptionsStatus)

-- | IAM access policy as a JSON-formatted string.
domainConfig_accessPolicies :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe AccessPoliciesStatus)

-- | Specifies <tt>AutoTuneOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_autoTuneOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe AutoTuneOptionsStatus)

-- | Log publishing options for the given domain.
domainConfig_logPublishingOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe LogPublishingOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>ClusterConfig</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_clusterConfig :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe ClusterConfigStatus)

-- | Specifies <tt>AdvancedSecurityOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_advancedSecurityOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>SnapshotOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_snapshotOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe SnapshotOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>CognitoOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Configuring Amazon Cognito authentication for
--   OpenSearch Dashboards</a>.
domainConfig_cognitoOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe CognitoOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>EncryptionAtRestOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_encryptionAtRestOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>VPCOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Launching your Amazon OpenSearch Service domains
--   using a VPC</a>.
domainConfig_vPCOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe VPCDerivedInfoStatus)

-- | The <tt>DomainEndpointOptions</tt> for the domain.
domainConfig_domainEndpointOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe DomainEndpointOptionsStatus)

-- | The <tt>AdvancedOptions</tt> for the domain. See <a>Advanced
--   options</a> for more information.
domainConfig_advancedOptions :: Lens' DomainConfig (Maybe AdvancedOptionsStatus)

-- | Options to configure the endpoint for the domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDomainEndpointOptions</a> smart constructor.
data DomainEndpointOptions
DomainEndpointOptions' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe TLSSecurityPolicy -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> DomainEndpointOptions

-- | Whether only HTTPS endpoint should be enabled for the domain.
[$sel:enforceHTTPS:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specify the TLS security policy to apply to the HTTPS endpoint of the
--   domain. Can be one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-0-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports TLSv1.0 and higher.</li>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-2-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports only TLSv1.2</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:tLSSecurityPolicy:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe TLSSecurityPolicy

-- | Whether to enable a custom endpoint for the domain.
[$sel:customEndpointEnabled:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | The fully qualified domain for your custom endpoint.
[$sel:customEndpoint:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | The ACM certificate ARN for your custom endpoint.
[$sel:customEndpointCertificateArn:DomainEndpointOptions'] :: DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DomainEndpointOptions</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:enforceHTTPS:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_enforceHTTPS</a> - Whether only HTTPS
--   endpoint should be enabled for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tLSSecurityPolicy:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_tLSSecurityPolicy</a> - Specify the TLS
--   security policy to apply to the HTTPS endpoint of the domain. Can be
--   one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-0-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports TLSv1.0 and higher.</li>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-2-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports only TLSv1.2</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:customEndpointEnabled:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointEnabled</a> - Whether to enable
--   a custom endpoint for the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customEndpoint:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_customEndpoint</a> - The fully qualified
--   domain for your custom endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:customEndpointCertificateArn:DomainEndpointOptions'</a>,
--   <a>domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointCertificateArn</a> - The ACM
--   certificate ARN for your custom endpoint.
newDomainEndpointOptions :: DomainEndpointOptions

-- | Whether only HTTPS endpoint should be enabled for the domain.
domainEndpointOptions_enforceHTTPS :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specify the TLS security policy to apply to the HTTPS endpoint of the
--   domain. Can be one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-0-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports TLSv1.0 and higher.</li>
--   <li><b>Policy-Min-TLS-1-2-2019-07:</b> TLS security policy which
--   supports only TLSv1.2</li>
--   </ul>

domainEndpointOptions_customEndpoint :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Text)

-- | The ACM certificate ARN for your custom endpoint.
domainEndpointOptions_customEndpointCertificateArn :: Lens' DomainEndpointOptions (Maybe Text)

-- | Information on a package associated with a domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDomainPackageDetails</a> smart constructor.
data DomainPackageDetails
DomainPackageDetails' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe PackageType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe DomainPackageStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ErrorDetails -> Maybe Text -> DomainPackageDetails

-- | The timestamp of the most recent update to the package association
--   status.
[$sel:lastUpdated:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The internal ID of the package.
[$sel:packageID:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Currently supports only TXT-DICTIONARY.
[$sel:packageType:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe PackageType

-- | User-specified name of the package.
[$sel:packageName:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text
[$sel:packageVersion:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | State of the association. Values are ASSOCIATING, ASSOCIATION_FAILED,
--   ACTIVE, DISSOCIATING, and DISSOCIATION_FAILED.
[$sel:domainPackageStatus:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe DomainPackageStatus

-- | The name of the domain you've associated a package with.
[$sel:domainName:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Additional information if the package is in an error state. Null
--   otherwise.
[$sel:errorDetails:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe ErrorDetails

-- | The relative path on Amazon OpenSearch Service nodes, which can be
--   used as synonym_path when the package is a synonym file.
[$sel:referencePath:DomainPackageDetails'] :: DomainPackageDetails -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>DomainPackageDetails</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdated:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_lastUpdated</a> - The timestamp of the most
--   recent update to the package association status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageID:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageID</a> - The internal ID of the
--   package.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageType:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageType</a> - Currently supports only
--   TXT-DICTIONARY.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageName:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageName</a> - User-specified name of the
--   package.
--   
--   <a>$sel:packageVersion:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_packageVersion</a> - Undocumented member.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainPackageStatus:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_domainPackageStatus</a> - State of the
--   association. Values are ASSOCIATING, ASSOCIATION_FAILED, ACTIVE,
--   DISSOCIATING, and DISSOCIATION_FAILED.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainName:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_domainName</a> - The name of the domain you've
--   associated a package with.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorDetails:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_errorDetails</a> - Additional information if
--   the package is in an error state. Null otherwise.
--   
--   <a>$sel:referencePath:DomainPackageDetails'</a>,
--   <a>domainPackageDetails_referencePath</a> - The relative path on
--   Amazon OpenSearch Service nodes, which can be used as synonym_path
--   when the package is a synonym file.
newDomainPackageDetails :: DomainPackageDetails

--   status.
domainPackageDetails_lastUpdated :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe UTCTime)

domainPackageDetails_packageID :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)

--   ACTIVE, DISSOCIATING, and DISSOCIATION_FAILED.

-- | The name of the domain you've associated a package with.
domainPackageDetails_domainName :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe Text)

-- | Additional information if the package is in an error state. Null
--   otherwise.
domainPackageDetails_errorDetails :: Lens' DomainPackageDetails (Maybe ErrorDetails)

--   used as synonym_path when the package is a synonym file.

-- | The current status of a domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDomainStatus</a> smart constructor.
data DomainStatus
DomainStatus' :: Maybe EBSOptions -> Maybe Text -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe AutoTuneOptionsOutput -> Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption) -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe SnapshotOptions -> Maybe CognitoOptions -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe VPCDerivedInfo -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text) -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text) -> Text -> Text -> Text -> ClusterConfig -> DomainStatus

-- | The <tt>EBSOptions</tt> for the specified domain.
[$sel:eBSOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe EBSOptions
[$sel:engineVersion:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The status of the <tt>NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</tt>.
[$sel:nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions

-- | IAM access policy as a JSON-formatted string.
[$sel:accessPolicies:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The current status of the domain's service software.
[$sel:serviceSoftwareOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe ServiceSoftwareOptions

-- | The current status of the domain's Auto-Tune options.
[$sel:autoTuneOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe AutoTuneOptionsOutput

-- | Log publishing options for the given domain.
[$sel:logPublishingOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption)

-- | The current status of the domain's advanced security options.
[$sel:advancedSecurityOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptions

-- | The domain creation status. <tt>True</tt> if the creation of a domain
--   is complete. <tt> False </tt> if domain creation is still in progress.
[$sel:created:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The status of the <tt>SnapshotOptions</tt>.
[$sel:snapshotOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe SnapshotOptions

-- | The <tt>CognitoOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Configuring Amazon Cognito authentication for
--   OpenSearch Dashboards</a>.
[$sel:cognitoOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe CognitoOptions

-- | The status of the <tt>EncryptionAtRestOptions</tt>.
[$sel:encryptionAtRestOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptions

-- | The domain deletion status. <tt>True</tt> if a delete request has been
--   received for the domain but resource cleanup is still in progress.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the domain has not been deleted. Once domain
--   deletion is complete, the status of the domain is no longer returned.
[$sel:deleted:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The <tt>VPCOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Launching your Amazon OpenSearch Service domains
--   using a VPC</a>.
[$sel:vPCOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe VPCDerivedInfo

-- | Map containing the domain endpoints used to submit index and search
--   requests. Example <tt>key, value</tt>:
--   <tt>'vpc','vpc-endpoint-h2dsd34efgyghrtguk5gt6j2foh4.us-east-1.es.amazonaws.com'</tt>.
[$sel:endpoints:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text)

-- | The current status of the domain's endpoint options.
[$sel:domainEndpointOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptions

-- | The status of the domain configuration. <tt>True</tt> if Amazon
--   OpenSearch Service is processing configuration changes. <tt>False</tt>
--   if the configuration is active.
[$sel:processing:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The domain endpoint that you use to submit index and search requests.
[$sel:endpoint:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The status of a domain version upgrade. <tt>True</tt> if Amazon
--   OpenSearch Service is undergoing a version upgrade. <tt>False</tt> if
--   the configuration is active.
[$sel:upgradeProcessing:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The status of the <tt>AdvancedOptions</tt>.
[$sel:advancedOptions:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text)

-- | The unique identifier for the specified domain.
[$sel:domainId:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Text

-- | The name of a domain. Domain names are unique across the domains owned
--   by an account within an AWS region. Domain names start with a letter
--   or number and can contain the following characters: a-z (lowercase),
--   0-9, and - (hyphen).
[$sel:domainName:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a domain. See <a>IAM identifiers</a>
--   in the <i>AWS Identity and Access Management User Guide</i> for more
--   information.
[$sel:arn:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> Text

-- | The type and number of instances in the domain.
[$sel:clusterConfig:DomainStatus'] :: DomainStatus -> ClusterConfig

-- | Create a value of <a>DomainStatus</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:eBSOptions:DomainStatus'</a>, <a>domainStatus_eBSOptions</a> -
--   The <tt>EBSOptions</tt> for the specified domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:engineVersion:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_engineVersion</a> - Undocumented member.
--   
--   <a>$sel:nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</a> - The status of the
--   <tt>NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:accessPolicies:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_accessPolicies</a> - IAM access policy as a
--   JSON-formatted string.
--   
--   <a>$sel:serviceSoftwareOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_serviceSoftwareOptions</a> - The current status of the
--   domain's service software.
--   
--   <a>$sel:autoTuneOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_autoTuneOptions</a> - The current status of the
--   domain's Auto-Tune options.
--

--   <a>domainStatus_logPublishingOptions</a> - Log publishing options for
--   the given domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:advancedSecurityOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_advancedSecurityOptions</a> - The current status of
--   the domain's advanced security options.
--

--   domain creation status. <tt>True</tt> if the creation of a domain is
--   complete. <tt> False </tt> if domain creation is still in progress.

--   <a>$sel:deleted:DomainStatus'</a>, <a>domainStatus_deleted</a> - The
--   domain deletion status. <tt>True</tt> if a delete request has been
--   received for the domain but resource cleanup is still in progress.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the domain has not been deleted. Once domain
--   deletion is complete, the status of the domain is no longer returned.
--   
--   <a>$sel:vPCOptions:DomainStatus'</a>, <a>domainStatus_vPCOptions</a> -
--   The <tt>VPCOptions</tt> for the specified domain. For more
--   information, see <a>Launching your Amazon OpenSearch Service domains
--   using a VPC</a>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endpoints:DomainStatus'</a>, <a>domainStatus_endpoints</a> -
--   Map containing the domain endpoints used to submit index and search
--   requests. Example <tt>key, value</tt>:
--   <tt>'vpc','vpc-endpoint-h2dsd34efgyghrtguk5gt6j2foh4.us-east-1.es.amazonaws.com'</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainEndpointOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,

--

--   The status of the domain configuration. <tt>True</tt> if Amazon
--   OpenSearch Service is processing configuration changes. <tt>False</tt>
--   if the configuration is active.
--   
--   <a>$sel:endpoint:DomainStatus'</a>, <a>domainStatus_endpoint</a> - The
--   domain endpoint that you use to submit index and search requests.
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeProcessing:DomainStatus'</a>,

--   upgrade. <tt>True</tt> if Amazon OpenSearch Service is undergoing a

--   <a>$sel:advancedOptions:DomainStatus'</a>,
--   <a>domainStatus_advancedOptions</a> - The status of the
--   <tt>AdvancedOptions</tt>.
--

--   unique identifier for the specified domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:domainName:DomainStatus'</a>, <a>domainStatus_domainName</a> -
--   The name of a domain. Domain names are unique across the domains owned
--   by an account within an AWS region. Domain names start with a letter
--   or number and can contain the following characters: a-z (lowercase),

--   information.
--   
--   <a>$sel:clusterConfig:DomainStatus'</a>,

--   in the domain.

domainStatus_snapshotOptions :: Lens' DomainStatus (Maybe SnapshotOptions)

-- | The domain deletion status. <tt>True</tt> if a delete request has been
--   received for the domain but resource cleanup is still in progress.
--   <tt>False</tt> if the domain has not been deleted. Once domain
--   deletion is complete, the status of the domain is no longer returned.

--   using a VPC</a>.
domainStatus_vPCOptions :: Lens' DomainStatus (Maybe VPCDerivedInfo)

domainStatus_domainEndpointOptions :: Lens' DomainStatus (Maybe DomainEndpointOptions)

--   OpenSearch Service is processing configuration changes. <tt>False</tt>
--   if the configuration is active.

domainStatus_endpoint :: Lens' DomainStatus (Maybe Text)

--   OpenSearch Service is undergoing a version upgrade. <tt>False</tt> if
--   the configuration is active.

domainStatus_domainId :: Lens' DomainStatus Text

-- | The name of a domain. Domain names are unique across the domains owned

--   or number and can contain the following characters: a-z (lowercase),

-- | The connection status of an inbound cross-cluster connection.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newInboundConnectionStatus</a> smart constructor.
data InboundConnectionStatus
InboundConnectionStatus' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe InboundConnectionStatusCode -> InboundConnectionStatus

-- | Verbose information for the inbound connection status.
[$sel:message:InboundConnectionStatus'] :: InboundConnectionStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The state code for the inbound connection. Can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by the
--   remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by the remote
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Inbound connection provisioning is in progress.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Inbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Inbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:statusCode:InboundConnectionStatus'] :: InboundConnectionStatus -> Maybe InboundConnectionStatusCode

-- | Create a value of <a>InboundConnectionStatus</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:InboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>inboundConnectionStatus_message</a> - Verbose information for the
--   inbound connection status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusCode:InboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>inboundConnectionStatus_statusCode</a> - The state code for the
--   inbound connection. Can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by the
--   remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by the remote
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Inbound connection provisioning is in progress.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Inbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Inbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
newInboundConnectionStatus :: InboundConnectionStatus

-- | Verbose information for the inbound connection status.
inboundConnectionStatus_message :: Lens' InboundConnectionStatus (Maybe Text)

-- | The state code for the inbound connection. Can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by the
--   remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by the remote
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Inbound connection provisioning is in progress.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Inbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Inbound connection is deleted and can no longer be

-- | Provides the current status of the entity.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOptionStatus</a> smart constructor.
data OptionStatus
OptionStatus' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Natural -> POSIX -> POSIX -> OptionState -> OptionStatus

-- | Indicates whether the domain is being deleted.
[$sel:pendingDeletion:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> Maybe Bool

-- | The latest version of the entity.
[$sel:updateVersion:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> Maybe Natural

[$sel:creationDate:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> POSIX

-- | The timestamp of the last time the entity was updated.
[$sel:updateDate:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> POSIX

[$sel:state:OptionStatus'] :: OptionStatus -> OptionState

-- | Create a value of <a>OptionStatus</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--

--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:

--   being deleted.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateVersion:OptionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>optionStatus_updateVersion</a> - The latest version of the entity.
--   
--   <a>$sel:creationDate:OptionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>optionStatus_creationDate</a> - The timestamp of when the entity
--   was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateDate:OptionStatus'</a>, <a>optionStatus_updateDate</a> -
--   The timestamp of the last time the entity was updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:state:OptionStatus'</a>, <a>optionStatus_state</a> - Provides
--   the <tt>OptionState</tt> for the domain.

-- | The connection status of an outbound cross-cluster connection.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOutboundConnectionStatus</a> smart constructor.
data OutboundConnectionStatus
OutboundConnectionStatus' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe OutboundConnectionStatusCode -> OutboundConnectionStatus

-- | Verbose information for the outbound connection status.
[$sel:message:OutboundConnectionStatus'] :: OutboundConnectionStatus -> Maybe Text

-- | The state code for the outbound connection. Can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by the remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Outbound connection has been approved by the remote
--   domain owner for getting provisioned.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Outbound connection rejection by remote domain owner is
--   in progress.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by remote domain
--   owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:statusCode:OutboundConnectionStatus'] :: OutboundConnectionStatus -> Maybe OutboundConnectionStatusCode

-- | Create a value of <a>OutboundConnectionStatus</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:OutboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>outboundConnectionStatus_message</a> - Verbose information for the
--   outbound connection status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusCode:OutboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>outboundConnectionStatus_statusCode</a> - The state code for the
--   outbound connection. Can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by the remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Outbound connection has been approved by the remote
--   domain owner for getting provisioned.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Outbound connection rejection by remote domain owner is
--   in progress.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by remote domain
--   owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
newOutboundConnectionStatus :: OutboundConnectionStatus

-- | Verbose information for the outbound connection status.
outboundConnectionStatus_message :: Lens' OutboundConnectionStatus (Maybe Text)

-- | The state code for the outbound connection. Can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by the remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Outbound connection has been approved by the remote
--   domain owner for getting provisioned.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Outbound connection rejection by remote domain owner is
--   in progress.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by remote domain
--   owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
outboundConnectionStatus_statusCode :: Lens' OutboundConnectionStatus (Maybe OutboundConnectionStatusCode)

recurringCharge_recurringChargeFrequency :: Lens' RecurringCharge (Maybe Text)

-- | Details of a reserved OpenSearch instance.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newReservedInstance</a> smart constructor.
data ReservedInstance
ReservedInstance' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Int -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe OpenSearchPartitionInstanceType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Integer -> Maybe [RecurringCharge] -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Double -> Maybe Int -> Maybe ReservedInstancePaymentOption -> ReservedInstance

--   offering.

[$sel:billingSubscriptionId:ReservedInstance'] :: ReservedInstance -> Maybe Integer

--   domains using the instance offering.

--   this reserved instance.

--   offering.

-- | The current options of an domain service software options.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newServiceSoftwareOptions</a> smart constructor.
data ServiceSoftwareOptions
ServiceSoftwareOptions' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe DeploymentStatus -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ServiceSoftwareOptions

-- | The timestamp, in Epoch time, until which you can manually request a
--   service software update. After this date, we automatically update your
--   service software.
[$sel:automatedUpdateDate:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The current service software version present on the domain.
[$sel:currentVersion:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | <tt>True</tt> if a service software is never automatically updated.
--   <tt>False</tt> if a service software is automatically updated after
--   <tt>AutomatedUpdateDate</tt>.
[$sel:optionalDeployment:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | The status of your service software update. This field can take the
--   following values: <tt> ELIGIBLE</tt>, <tt>PENDING_UPDATE</tt>,
--   <tt>IN_PROGRESS</tt>, <tt>COMPLETED</tt>, and <tt> NOT_ELIGIBLE</tt>.
[$sel:updateStatus:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe DeploymentStatus

-- | <tt>True</tt> if you're able to cancel your service software version
--   update. <tt>False</tt> if you can't cancel your service software
--   update.
[$sel:cancellable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | <tt>True</tt> if you're able to update your service software version.
--   <tt>False</tt> if you can't update your service software version.
[$sel:updateAvailable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Bool

-- | The description of the <tt>UpdateStatus</tt>.
[$sel:description:ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | The new service software version if one is available.
[$sel:newVersion':ServiceSoftwareOptions'] :: ServiceSoftwareOptions -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ServiceSoftwareOptions</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:automatedUpdateDate:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_automatedUpdateDate</a> - The timestamp, in
--   Epoch time, until which you can manually request a service software
--   update. After this date, we automatically update your service
--   software.
--   
--   <a>$sel:currentVersion:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_currentVersion</a> - The current service
--   software version present on the domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:optionalDeployment:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_optionalDeployment</a> - <tt>True</tt> if a
--   service software is never automatically updated. <tt>False</tt> if a
--   service software is automatically updated after
--   <tt>AutomatedUpdateDate</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateStatus:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_updateStatus</a> - The status of your
--   service software update. This field can take the following values:
--   <tt> ELIGIBLE</tt>, <tt>PENDING_UPDATE</tt>, <tt>IN_PROGRESS</tt>,
--   <tt>COMPLETED</tt>, and <tt> NOT_ELIGIBLE</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:cancellable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_cancellable</a> - <tt>True</tt> if you're
--   able to cancel your service software version update. <tt>False</tt> if
--   you can't cancel your service software update.
--   
--   <a>$sel:updateAvailable:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_updateAvailable</a> - <tt>True</tt> if
--   you're able to update your service software version. <tt>False</tt> if
--   you can't update your service software version.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_description</a> - The description of the
--   <tt>UpdateStatus</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:newVersion':ServiceSoftwareOptions'</a>,
--   <a>serviceSoftwareOptions_newVersion</a> - The new service software
--   version if one is available.
newServiceSoftwareOptions :: ServiceSoftwareOptions

-- | The timestamp, in Epoch time, until which you can manually request a
--   service software update. After this date, we automatically update your
--   service software.
serviceSoftwareOptions_automatedUpdateDate :: Lens' ServiceSoftwareOptions (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The current service software version present on the domain.
serviceSoftwareOptions_currentVersion :: Lens' ServiceSoftwareOptions (Maybe Text)

-- | <tt>True</tt> if a service software is never automatically updated.
--   <tt>False</tt> if a service software is automatically updated after
--   <tt>AutomatedUpdateDate</tt>.
serviceSoftwareOptions_optionalDeployment :: Lens' ServiceSoftwareOptions (Maybe Bool)

-- | The status of your service software update. This field can take the
--   following values: <tt> ELIGIBLE</tt>, <tt>PENDING_UPDATE</tt>,
--   <tt>IN_PROGRESS</tt>, <tt>COMPLETED</tt>, and <tt> NOT_ELIGIBLE</tt>.
serviceSoftwareOptions_updateStatus :: Lens' ServiceSoftwareOptions (Maybe DeploymentStatus)

-- | <tt>True</tt> if you're able to cancel your service software version
--   update. <tt>False</tt> if you can't cancel your service software
--   update.
serviceSoftwareOptions_cancellable :: Lens' ServiceSoftwareOptions (Maybe Bool)

-- | <tt>True</tt> if you're able to update your service software version.
--   <tt>False</tt> if you can't update your service software version.
serviceSoftwareOptions_updateAvailable :: Lens' ServiceSoftwareOptions (Maybe Bool)

-- | The description of the <tt>UpdateStatus</tt>.
serviceSoftwareOptions_description :: Lens' ServiceSoftwareOptions (Maybe Text)

-- | The new service software version if one is available.
serviceSoftwareOptions_newVersion :: Lens' ServiceSoftwareOptions (Maybe Text)

-- | A key value pair for a resource tag.

--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTag</a> smart constructor.
data Tag

--   the domain to which they are attached.

-- | The <tt>TagValue</tt>, the value assigned to the corresponding tag
--   key. Tag values can be null and don't have to be unique in a tag set.
--   For example, you can have a key value pair in a tag set of <tt>project
--   : Trinity</tt> and <tt>cost-center : Trinity</tt>
[$sel:value:Tag'] :: Tag -> Text

--   of the tag. Tag keys must be unique for the domain to which they are
--   attached.
--   
--   <a>$sel:value:Tag'</a>, <a>tag_value</a> - The <tt>TagValue</tt>, the
--   value assigned to the corresponding tag key. Tag values can be null
--   and don't have to be unique in a tag set. For example, you can have a
--   key value pair in a tag set of <tt>project : Trinity</tt> and
--   <tt>cost-center : Trinity</tt>

-- | History of the last 10 upgrades and upgrade eligibility checks.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpgradeHistory</a> smart constructor.
data UpgradeHistory
UpgradeHistory' :: Maybe UpgradeStatus -> Maybe [UpgradeStepItem] -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> UpgradeHistory

-- | The current status of the upgrade. The status can take one of the
--   following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
[$sel:upgradeStatus:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe UpgradeStatus

--   each step performed as part of a specific upgrade or upgrade
--   eligibility check.
[$sel:stepsList:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe [UpgradeStepItem]

-- | A string that briefly describes the upgrade.
[$sel:upgradeName:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe Text

-- | UTC timestamp at which the upgrade API call was made in
--   "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ" format.
[$sel:startTimestamp:UpgradeHistory'] :: UpgradeHistory -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Create a value of <a>UpgradeHistory</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.

--   upgrade. The status can take one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>
--   
--   <a>$sel:stepsList:UpgradeHistory'</a>, <a>upgradeHistory_stepsList</a>
--   - A list of <tt> UpgradeStepItem </tt> s representing information
--   about each step performed as part of a specific upgrade or upgrade
--   eligibility check.
--   
--   <a>$sel:upgradeName:UpgradeHistory'</a>,
--   <a>upgradeHistory_upgradeName</a> - A string that briefly describes
--   the upgrade.
--   
--   <a>$sel:startTimestamp:UpgradeHistory'</a>,

--   upgrade API call was made in "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ" format.
newUpgradeHistory :: UpgradeHistory

--   following values:
--

-- | Represents a single step of the upgrade or upgrade eligibility check
--   workflow.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpgradeStepItem</a> smart constructor.
data UpgradeStepItem

--   following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>

--   particular step.

--   encountered in a particular step.

-- | One of three steps an upgrade or upgrade eligibility check goes
--   through:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PreUpgradeCheck</li>
--   <li>Snapshot</li>
--   <li>Upgrade</li>
--   </ul>

--   </ul>

-- | Schedules a service software update for an Amazon OpenSearch Service
--   domain.
module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.StartServiceSoftwareUpdate

-- | Container for the parameters to the <tt> StartServiceSoftwareUpdate
--   </tt> operation. Specifies the name of the domain to schedule a

-- | Container for the parameters to the <tt> ListVersions </tt> operation.
--   
--   Use <tt> MaxResults </tt> to control the maximum number of results to
--   retrieve in a single call.
--   
--   Use <tt> NextToken </tt> in response to retrieve more results. If the
--   received response does not contain a NextToken, there are no more
--   results to retrieve.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newListVersions</a> smart constructor.

-- | Retrieves the latest status of the last upgrade or upgrade eligibility
--   check performed on the domain.
module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.GetUpgradeStatus

--   </tt> operation.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newGetUpgradeStatus</a> smart constructor.

-- | One of four statuses an upgrade have, returned as part of the <tt>
--   GetUpgradeStatusResponse </tt> object. The status can take one of the
--   following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>

--   through:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PreUpgradeCheck</li>
--   <li>Snapshot</li>
--   <li>Upgrade</li>
--   </ul>

--   connections. Available <tt> Filter </tt> names for this operation are:
--

--   <li>connection-id</li>

--   connections. Available <tt> Filter </tt> values are:

--   <li>connection-id</li>
--   <li>local-domain-info.domain-name</li>

--   </ul>

-- | Creates a new Amazon OpenSearch Service domain. For more information,
--   see <a>Creating and managing Amazon OpenSearch Service domains</a> in
--   the <i>Amazon OpenSearch Service Developer Guide</i>.
module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.CreateDomain

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newCreateDomain</a> smart constructor.
data CreateDomain
CreateDomain' :: Maybe EBSOptions -> Maybe Text -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions -> Maybe Text -> Maybe AutoTuneOptionsInput -> Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption) -> Maybe ClusterConfig -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptionsInput -> Maybe [Tag] -> Maybe SnapshotOptions -> Maybe CognitoOptions -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptions -> Maybe VPCOptions -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text) -> Text -> CreateDomain

-- | Options to enable, disable, and specify the type and size of EBS
--   storage volumes.
[$sel:eBSOptions:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe EBSOptions

-- | String of format Elasticsearch_X.Y or OpenSearch_X.Y to specify the
--   engine version for the Amazon OpenSearch Service domain. For example,
--   "OpenSearch_1.0" or "Elasticsearch_7.9". For more information, see
--   <a>Creating and managing Amazon OpenSearch Service domains</a> .
[$sel:engineVersion:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe Text

-- | Node-to-node encryption options.
[$sel:nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions

-- | IAM access policy as a JSON-formatted string.
[$sel:accessPolicies:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies Auto-Tune options.
[$sel:autoTuneOptions:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe AutoTuneOptionsInput

-- | Map of <tt>LogType</tt> and <tt>LogPublishingOption</tt>, each
--   containing options to publish a given type of OpenSearch log.
[$sel:logPublishingOptions:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption)

-- | Configuration options for a domain. Specifies the instance type and
--   number of instances in the domain.
[$sel:clusterConfig:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe ClusterConfig

-- | Specifies advanced security options.
[$sel:advancedSecurityOptions:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptionsInput

-- | A list of <tt>Tag</tt> added during domain creation.
[$sel:tagList:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe [Tag]

-- | Option to set time, in UTC format, of the daily automated snapshot.
--   Default value is 0 hours.
[$sel:snapshotOptions:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe SnapshotOptions

-- | Options to specify the Cognito user and identity pools for OpenSearch
--   Dashboards authentication. For more information, see <a>Configuring
--   Amazon Cognito authentication for OpenSearch Dashboards</a>.
[$sel:cognitoOptions:CreateDomain'] :: CreateDomain -> Maybe CognitoOptions

--   endpoint.

-- | Option to allow references to indices in an HTTP request body. Must be

--   default, the value is <tt>true</tt>. See <a>Advanced cluster
--   parameters</a> for more information.

-- | Attaches tags to an existing domain. Tags are a set of case-sensitive
--   key value pairs. An domain can have up to 10 tags. See <a>Tagging
--   Amazon OpenSearch Service domains</a> for more information.
module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.AddTags

-- | Container for the parameters to the <tt> AddTags </tt> operation.
--   Specifies the tags to attach to the domain.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newAddTags</a> smart constructor.
data AddTags
AddTags' :: Text -> [Tag] -> AddTags

-- | Specify the <tt>ARN</tt> of the domain you want to add tags to.
[$sel:arn:AddTags'] :: AddTags -> Text

-- | List of <tt>Tag</tt> to add to the domain.
[$sel:tagList:AddTags'] :: AddTags -> [Tag]

-- | Create a value of <a>AddTags</a> with all optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:arn:AddTags'</a>, <a>addTags_arn</a> - Specify the
--   <tt>ARN</tt> of the domain you want to add tags to.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tagList:AddTags'</a>, <a>addTags_tagList</a> - List of
--   <tt>Tag</tt> to add to the domain.
newAddTags :: Text -> AddTags

-- | Specify the <tt>ARN</tt> of the domain you want to add tags to.
addTags_arn :: Lens' AddTags Text

-- | List of <tt>Tag</tt> to add to the domain.
addTags_tagList :: Lens' AddTags [Tag]

-- | <i>See:</i> <a>newAddTagsResponse</a> smart constructor.
data AddTagsResponse

-- | Create a value of <a>AddTagsResponse</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
newAddTagsResponse :: AddTagsResponse

instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.OpenSearch.AddTags.AddTags

-- | Modifies the cluster configuration of the specified domain, such as
--   setting the instance type and the number of instances.
module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.UpdateDomainConfig

-- | Container for the parameters to the <tt> UpdateDomain </tt> operation.
--   Specifies the type and number of instances in the domain cluster.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpdateDomainConfig</a> smart constructor.
data UpdateDomainConfig
UpdateDomainConfig' :: Maybe EBSOptions -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions -> Maybe Text -> Maybe AutoTuneOptions -> Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption) -> Maybe ClusterConfig -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptionsInput -> Maybe SnapshotOptions -> Maybe CognitoOptions -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptions -> Maybe VPCOptions -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptions -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text) -> Text -> UpdateDomainConfig

-- | Specify the type and size of the EBS volume to use.
[$sel:eBSOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe EBSOptions

-- | Specifies node-to-node encryption options.
[$sel:nodeToNodeEncryptionOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe NodeToNodeEncryptionOptions

-- | IAM access policy as a JSON-formatted string.
[$sel:accessPolicies:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies Auto-Tune options.
[$sel:autoTuneOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe AutoTuneOptions

-- | Map of <tt>LogType</tt> and <tt>LogPublishingOption</tt>, each
--   containing options to publish a given type of OpenSearch log.
[$sel:logPublishingOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe (HashMap LogType LogPublishingOption)

-- | The type and number of instances to instantiate for the domain
--   cluster.
[$sel:clusterConfig:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe ClusterConfig

-- | Specifies advanced security options.
[$sel:advancedSecurityOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe AdvancedSecurityOptionsInput

-- | Option to set the time, in UTC format, for the daily automated
--   snapshot. Default value is <tt>0</tt> hours.
[$sel:snapshotOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe SnapshotOptions

-- | Options to specify the Cognito user and identity pools for OpenSearch
--   Dashboards authentication. For more information, see <a>Configuring
--   Amazon Cognito authentication for OpenSearch Dashboards</a>.
[$sel:cognitoOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe CognitoOptions

-- | Specifies encryption of data at rest options.
[$sel:encryptionAtRestOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe EncryptionAtRestOptions

-- | Options to specify the subnets and security groups for the VPC
--   endpoint. For more information, see <a>Launching your Amazon
--   OpenSearch Service domains using a VPC</a> .
[$sel:vPCOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe VPCOptions

-- | Options to specify configuration that will be applied to the domain
--   endpoint.
[$sel:domainEndpointOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe DomainEndpointOptions

-- | Modifies the advanced option to allow references to indices in an HTTP
--   request body. Must be <tt>false</tt> when configuring access to
--   individual sub-resources. By default, the value is <tt>true</tt>. See
--   <a>Advanced options</a> for more information.
[$sel:advancedOptions:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text)

-- | The name of the domain you're updating.
[$sel:domainName:UpdateDomainConfig'] :: UpdateDomainConfig -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>UpdateDomainConfig</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   the EBS volume to use.

--   security options.

-- | Allows you to either upgrade your domain or perform an upgrade
--   eligibility check to a compatible version of OpenSearch or
--   Elasticsearch.
module Network.AWS.OpenSearch.UpgradeDomain

-- | Container for the request parameters to <tt> UpgradeDomain </tt>
--   operation.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newUpgradeDomain</a> smart constructor.
data UpgradeDomain
UpgradeDomain' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text) -> Text -> Text -> UpgradeDomain

--   performed. Does not actually perform the upgrade.
[$sel:performCheckOnly:UpgradeDomain'] :: UpgradeDomain -> Maybe Bool
[$sel:advancedOptions:UpgradeDomain'] :: UpgradeDomain -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text)
[$sel:domainName:UpgradeDomain'] :: UpgradeDomain -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>UpgradeDomain</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.

--   intend to upgrade the domain to.

-- | The version of OpenSearch that you intend to upgrade the domain to.

upgradeDomainResponse_httpStatus :: Lens' UpgradeDomainResponse Int

-- | The state code for the inbound connection. Can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by the
--   remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by the remote
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Inbound connection provisioning is in progress.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Inbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Inbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>

-- | The state code for the outbound connection. Can be one of the
--   following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by the remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Outbound connection has been approved by the remote
--   domain owner for getting provisioned.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Outbound connection rejection by remote domain owner is
--   in progress.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by remote domain
--   owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
outboundConnectionStatus_statusCode :: Lens' OutboundConnectionStatus (Maybe OutboundConnectionStatusCode)

--   code of 400.

--   resource. Returns HTTP status code 403.
_AccessDeniedException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

--   status code of 400.

--   that is currently in use. Returns HTTP status code 409.
_ConflictException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An error occurred while processing the request.
_BaseException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

-- | An error occured because the client wanted to access a not supported
--   operation. Gives http status code of 409.
_DisabledOperationException :: AsError a => Getting (First ServiceError) a ServiceError

--   exception or failure (the failure is internal to the service) . Gives
--   http status code of 500.

--   either invalid or not supported. Gives http status code of 409.

--   sub-resources. Gives http status code of 409.

--   <a>$sel:localDomainInfo:CreateOutboundConnection'</a>,
--   <a>createOutboundConnection_localDomainInfo</a> - The <tt>
--   AWSDomainInformation </tt> for the local OpenSearch domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:remoteDomainInfo:CreateOutboundConnection'</a>,
--   <a>createOutboundConnection_remoteDomainInfo</a> - The <tt>
--   AWSDomainInformation </tt> for the remote OpenSearch domain.
--   
--   <a>$sel:connectionAlias:CreateOutboundConnection'</a>,
--   <a>createOutboundConnection_connectionAlias</a> - The connection alias
--   used used by the customer for this cross-cluster connection.
newCreateOutboundConnection :: DomainInformationContainer -> DomainInformationContainer -> Text -> CreateOutboundConnection

-- | The result of a <tt> CreateOutboundConnection </tt> request. Contains
--   the details about the newly created cross-cluster connection.

--   constructor.
data CreateOutboundConnectionResponse

--   fields.

--   <a>$sel:localDomainInfo:CreateOutboundConnection'</a>,

-- | Type of log file. Can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>INDEX_SLOW_LOGS: Index slow logs contain insert requests that took
--   more time than configured index query log threshold to execute.</li>
--   <li>SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS: Search slow logs contain search queries that
--   took more time than configured search query log threshold to
--   execute.</li>
--   <li>ES_APPLICATION_LOGS: OpenSearch application logs contain
--   information about errors and warnings raised during the operation of
--   the service and can be useful for troubleshooting.</li>
--   <li>AUDIT_LOGS: Audit logs contain records of user requests for access
--   from the domain.</li>
--   </ul>
newtype LogType
LogType' :: Text -> LogType
[fromLogType] :: LogType -> Text
pattern LogType_AUDIT_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_ES_APPLICATION_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_INDEX_SLOW_LOGS :: LogType
pattern LogType_SEARCH_SLOW_LOGS :: LogType

-- | The connection status of an inbound cross-cluster connection.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newInboundConnectionStatus</a> smart constructor.
data InboundConnectionStatus
InboundConnectionStatus' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe InboundConnectionStatusCode -> InboundConnectionStatus

-- | Create a value of <a>InboundConnectionStatus</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:InboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>inboundConnectionStatus_message</a> - Verbose information for the
--   inbound connection status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusCode:InboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>inboundConnectionStatus_statusCode</a> - The state code for the
--   inbound connection. Can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Inbound connection is not yet accepted by the
--   remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Inbound connection is pending acceptance by the remote
--   domain owner.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Inbound connection provisioning is in progress.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Inbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Inbound connection rejection is in process.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Inbound connection is rejected.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Inbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>

--   used.</li>

data OutboundConnectionStatus

-- | Create a value of <a>OutboundConnectionStatus</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:message:OutboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>outboundConnectionStatus_message</a> - Verbose information for the
--   outbound connection status.
--   
--   <a>$sel:statusCode:OutboundConnectionStatus'</a>,
--   <a>outboundConnectionStatus_statusCode</a> - The state code for the
--   outbound connection. Can be one of the following:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>VALIDATING: The outbound connection request is being
--   validated.</li>
--   <li>VALIDATION_FAILED: Validation failed for the connection
--   request.</li>
--   <li>PENDING_ACCEPTANCE: Outbound connection request is validated and
--   is not yet accepted by the remote domain owner.</li>
--   <li>APPROVED: Outbound connection has been approved by the remote
--   domain owner for getting provisioned.</li>
--   <li>PROVISIONING: Outbound connection request is in process.</li>
--   <li>ACTIVE: Outbound connection is active and ready to use.</li>
--   <li>REJECTING: Outbound connection rejection by remote domain owner is
--   in progress.</li>
--   <li>REJECTED: Outbound connection request is rejected by remote domain
--   owner.</li>
--   <li>DELETING: Outbound connection deletion is in progress.</li>
--   <li>DELETED: Outbound connection is deleted and can no longer be
--   used.</li>
--   </ul>
newOutboundConnectionStatus :: OutboundConnectionStatus

--   upgrade. The status can take one of the following values:
--   
--   <ul>
--   <li>In Progress</li>
--   <li>Succeeded</li>
--   <li>Succeeded with Issues</li>
--   <li>Failed</li>
--   </ul>

--   the upgrade.

--   <a>upgradeHistory_startTimestamp</a> - UTC timestamp at which the
--   upgrade API call was made in "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ" format.
newUpgradeHistory :: UpgradeHistory
